158Pagination::Mode paginationModeForRenderStyle(const RenderStyle& style)
159{
160 Overflow overflow = style.overflowY();
161 if (overflow != Overflow::PagedX && overflow != Overflow::PagedY)
162 return Pagination::Unpaginated;
163
164 bool isHorizontalWritingMode = style.isHorizontalWritingMode();
165 TextDirection textDirection = style.direction();
166 WritingMode writingMode = style.writingMode();
167
168 // paged-x always corresponds to LeftToRightPaginated or RightToLeftPaginated. If the WritingMode
169 // is horizontal, then we use TextDirection to choose between those options. If the WritingMode
170 // is vertical, then the direction of the verticality dictates the choice.
171 if (overflow == Overflow::PagedX) {
172 if ((isHorizontalWritingMode && textDirection == TextDirection::LTR) || writingMode == WritingMode::LeftToRight)
173 return Pagination::LeftToRightPaginated;
174 return Pagination::RightToLeftPaginated;
175 }
176
177 // paged-y always corresponds to TopToBottomPaginated or BottomToTopPaginated. If the WritingMode
178 // is horizontal, then the direction of the horizontality dictates the choice. If the WritingMode
179 // is vertical, then we use TextDirection to choose between those options.
180 if (writingMode == WritingMode::TopToBottom || (!isHorizontalWritingMode && textDirection == TextDirection::RTL))
181 return Pagination::TopToBottomPaginated;
182 return Pagination::BottomToTopPaginated;
183}

185FrameView::FrameView(Frame& frame)
186 : m_frame(frame)
187 , m_layoutContext(*this)
188 , m_updateEmbeddedObjectsTimer(*this, &FrameView::updateEmbeddedObjectsTimerFired)
189 , m_updateWidgetPositionsTimer(*this, &FrameView::updateWidgetPositionsTimerFired)
190 , m_delayedScrollEventTimer(*this, &FrameView::sendScrollEvent)
191 , m_delayedScrollToFocusedElementTimer(*this, &FrameView::scrollToFocusedElementTimerFired)
192 , m_speculativeTilingEnableTimer(*this, &FrameView::speculativeTilingEnableTimerFired)
193{
194 init();
195
196#if ENABLE(RUBBER_BANDING)
197 ScrollElasticity verticalElasticity = ScrollElasticityNone;
198 ScrollElasticity horizontalElasticity = ScrollElasticityNone;
199 if (m_frame->isMainFrame()) {
200 verticalElasticity = m_frame->page() ? m_frame->page()->verticalScrollElasticity() : ScrollElasticityAllowed;
201 horizontalElasticity = m_frame->page() ? m_frame->page()->horizontalScrollElasticity() : ScrollElasticityAllowed;
202 } else if (m_frame->settings().rubberBandingForSubScrollableRegionsEnabled()) {
203 verticalElasticity = ScrollElasticityAutomatic;
204 horizontalElasticity = ScrollElasticityAutomatic;
205 }
206
207 ScrollableArea::setVerticalScrollElasticity(verticalElasticity);
208 ScrollableArea::setHorizontalScrollElasticity(horizontalElasticity);
209#endif
210}

212Ref<FrameView> FrameView::create(Frame& frame)
213{
214 Ref<FrameView> view = adoptRef(*new FrameView(frame));
215 if (frame.page() && frame.page()->isVisible())
216 view->show();
217 return view;
218}
219
220Ref<FrameView> FrameView::create(Frame& frame, const IntSize& initialSize)
221{
222 Ref<FrameView> view = adoptRef(*new FrameView(frame));
223 view->Widget::setFrameRect(IntRect(view->location(), initialSize));
224 if (frame.page() && frame.page()->isVisible())
225 view->show();
226 return view;
227}
228
229FrameView::~FrameView()
230{
231 removeFromAXObjectCache();
232 resetScrollbars();
233
234 // Custom scrollbars should already be destroyed at this point
235 ASSERT(!horizontalScrollbar() || !horizontalScrollbar()->isCustomScrollbar());
236 ASSERT(!verticalScrollbar() || !verticalScrollbar()->isCustomScrollbar());
237
238 setHasHorizontalScrollbar(false); // Remove native scrollbars now before we lose the connection to the HostWindow.
239 setHasVerticalScrollbar(false);
240
241 ASSERT(!m_scrollCorner);
242
243 ASSERT(frame().view() != this || !frame().contentRenderer());
244}

246void FrameView::reset()
247{
248 m_cannotBlitToWindow = false;
249 m_isOverlapped = false;
250 m_contentIsOpaque = false;
251 m_updateEmbeddedObjectsTimer.stop();
252 m_wasScrolledByUser = false;
253 m_delayedScrollEventTimer.stop();
254 m_shouldScrollToFocusedElement = false;
255 m_delayedScrollToFocusedElementTimer.stop();
256 m_lastViewportSize = IntSize();
257 m_lastZoomFactor = 1.0f;
258 m_isTrackingRepaints = false;
259 m_trackedRepaintRects.clear();
260 m_lastPaintTime = MonotonicTime();
261 m_paintBehavior = PaintBehavior::Normal;
262 m_isPainting = false;
263 m_needsDeferredScrollbarsUpdate = false;
264 m_needsDeferredPositionScrollbarLayers = false;
265 m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor = nullptr;
266 resetLayoutMilestones();
267 layoutContext().reset();
268}

282void FrameView::removeFromAXObjectCache()
283{
284 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache()) {
285 if (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = frame().ownerElement())
286 cache->childrenChanged(owner->renderer());
287 cache->remove(this);
288 }
289}
290
291void FrameView::resetScrollbars()
292{
293 // FIXME: Do we really need this?
294 layoutContext().resetFirstLayoutFlag();
295 // Reset the document's scrollbars back to our defaults before we yield the floor.
296 setScrollbarsSuppressed(true);
297 if (m_canHaveScrollbars)
298 setScrollbarModes(ScrollbarAuto, ScrollbarAuto);
299 else
300 setScrollbarModes(ScrollbarAlwaysOff, ScrollbarAlwaysOff);
301 setScrollbarsSuppressed(false);
302}
303
304void FrameView::resetScrollbarsAndClearContentsSize()
305{
306 resetScrollbars();
307
308 LOG(Layout, "FrameView %p resetScrollbarsAndClearContentsSize", this);
309
310 setScrollbarsSuppressed(true);
311 setContentsSize(IntSize());
312 setScrollbarsSuppressed(false);
313}
314
315void FrameView::init()
316{
317 reset();
318
319 m_size = LayoutSize();
320
321 // Propagate the scrolling mode to the view.
322 auto* ownerElement = frame().ownerElement();
323 if (is<HTMLFrameElementBase>(ownerElement) && downcast<HTMLFrameElementBase>(*ownerElement).scrollingMode() == ScrollbarAlwaysOff)
324 setCanHaveScrollbars(false);
325
326 Page* page = frame().page();
327 if (page && page->chrome().client().shouldPaintEntireContents())
328 setPaintsEntireContents(true);
329}
330
331void FrameView::prepareForDetach()
332{
333 detachCustomScrollbars();
334 // When the view is no longer associated with a frame, it needs to be removed from the ax object cache
335 // right now, otherwise it won't be able to reach the topDocument()'s axObject cache later.
336 removeFromAXObjectCache();
337
338 if (auto scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator())
339 scrollingCoordinator->willDestroyScrollableArea(*this);
340}
341
342void FrameView::detachCustomScrollbars()
343{
344 Scrollbar* horizontalBar = horizontalScrollbar();
345 if (horizontalBar && horizontalBar->isCustomScrollbar())
346 setHasHorizontalScrollbar(false);
347
348 Scrollbar* verticalBar = verticalScrollbar();
349 if (verticalBar && verticalBar->isCustomScrollbar())
350 setHasVerticalScrollbar(false);
351
352 m_scrollCorner = nullptr;
353}

355void FrameView::recalculateScrollbarOverlayStyle()
356{
357 auto style = [this] {
358 if (auto page = frame().page()) {
359 if (auto clientStyle = page->chrome().client().preferredScrollbarOverlayStyle())
360 return *clientStyle;
361 }
362 auto background = documentBackgroundColor();
363 if (background.isVisible()) {
364 if (background.lightness() <= .5f)
365 return ScrollbarOverlayStyleLight;
366 } else {
367 if (useDarkAppearance())
368 return ScrollbarOverlayStyleLight;
369 }
370 return ScrollbarOverlayStyleDefault;
371 }();
372 if (scrollbarOverlayStyle() != style)
373 setScrollbarOverlayStyle(style);
374}

393void FrameView::clear()
394{
395 setCanBlitOnScroll(true);
396
397 reset();
398
399 setScrollbarsSuppressed(true);
400
401#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
402 // To avoid flashes of white, disable tile updates immediately when view is cleared at the beginning of a page load.
403 // Tiling will be re-enabled from UIKit via [WAKWindow setTilingMode:] when we have content to draw.
404 if (LegacyTileCache* tileCache = legacyTileCache())
405 tileCache->setTilingMode(LegacyTileCache::Disabled);
406#endif
407}

423void FrameView::invalidateRect(const IntRect& rect)
424{
425 if (!parent()) {
426 if (auto* page = frame().page())
427 page->chrome().invalidateContentsAndRootView(rect);
428 return;
429 }
430
431 auto* renderer = frame().ownerRenderer();
432 if (!renderer)
433 return;
434
435 IntRect repaintRect = rect;
436 repaintRect.moveBy(roundedIntPoint(renderer->contentBoxLocation()));
437 renderer->repaintRectangle(repaintRect);
438}
439
440void FrameView::setFrameRect(const IntRect& newRect)
441{
442 Ref<FrameView> protectedThis(*this);
443 IntRect oldRect = frameRect();
444 if (newRect == oldRect)
445 return;
446
447 // Every scroll that happens as the result of frame size change is programmatic.
448 auto oldScrollType = currentScrollType();
449 setCurrentScrollType(ScrollType::Programmatic);
450
451 ScrollView::setFrameRect(newRect);
452
453 updateScrollableAreaSet();
454
455 if (RenderView* renderView = this->renderView()) {
456 if (renderView->usesCompositing())
457 renderView->compositor().frameViewDidChangeSize();
458 }
459
460 if (frame().isMainFrame() && frame().page())
461 frame().page()->pageOverlayController().didChangeViewSize();
462
463 viewportContentsChanged();
464 setCurrentScrollType(oldScrollType);
465}

467FrameFlattening FrameView::effectiveFrameFlattening() const
468{
469#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
470 // On iOS when async frame scrolling is enabled, it does not make sense to use full frame flattening.
471 // In that case, we just consider that frame flattening is disabled. This allows people to test
472 // frame scrolling on iOS by enabling "Async Frame Scrolling" via the Safari menu.
473 if (frame().settings().asyncFrameScrollingEnabled() && frame().settings().frameFlattening() == FrameFlattening::FullyEnabled)
474 return FrameFlattening::Disabled;
475#endif
476 return frame().settings().frameFlattening();
477}
478
479bool FrameView::frameFlatteningEnabled() const
480{
481 return effectiveFrameFlattening() != FrameFlattening::Disabled;
482}
483
484bool FrameView::isFrameFlatteningValidForThisFrame() const
485{
486 if (!frameFlatteningEnabled())
487 return false;
488
489 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = frame().ownerElement();
490 if (!owner)
491 return false;
492
493 // Frame flattening is valid only for <frame> and <iframe>.
494 return owner->hasTagName(frameTag) || owner->hasTagName(iframeTag);
495}

497bool FrameView::avoidScrollbarCreation() const
498{
499 // with frame flattening no subframe can have scrollbars
500 // but we also cannot turn scrollbars off as we determine
501 // our flattening policy using that.
502 return isFrameFlatteningValidForThisFrame();
503}

511void FrameView::updateCanHaveScrollbars()
512{
513 ScrollbarMode hMode;
514 ScrollbarMode vMode;
515 scrollbarModes(hMode, vMode);
516 if (hMode == ScrollbarAlwaysOff && vMode == ScrollbarAlwaysOff)
517 setCanHaveScrollbars(false);
518 else
519 setCanHaveScrollbars(true);
520}

522RefPtr<Element> FrameView::rootElementForCustomScrollbarPartStyle(PseudoId partPseudoId) const
523{
524 // FIXME: We need to update the scrollbar dynamically as documents change (or as doc elements and bodies get discovered that have custom styles).
525 auto* document = frame().document();
526 if (!document)
527 return nullptr;
528
529 // Try the <body> element first as a scrollbar source.
530 auto* body = document->bodyOrFrameset();
531 if (body && body->renderer() && body->renderer()->style().hasPseudoStyle(partPseudoId))
532 return body;
533
534 // If the <body> didn't have a custom style, then the root element might.
535 auto* docElement = document->documentElement();
536 if (docElement && docElement->renderer() && docElement->renderer()->style().hasPseudoStyle(partPseudoId))
537 return docElement;
538
539 return nullptr;
540}
541
542Ref<Scrollbar> FrameView::createScrollbar(ScrollbarOrientation orientation)
543{
544 if (auto element = rootElementForCustomScrollbarPartStyle(PseudoId::Scrollbar))
545 return RenderScrollbar::createCustomScrollbar(*this, orientation, element.get());
546
547 // If we have an owning iframe/frame element, then it can set the custom scrollbar also.
548 // FIXME: Seems bad to do this for cross-origin frames.
549 RenderWidget* frameRenderer = frame().ownerRenderer();
550 if (frameRenderer && frameRenderer->style().hasPseudoStyle(PseudoId::Scrollbar))
551 return RenderScrollbar::createCustomScrollbar(*this, orientation, nullptr, &frame());
552
553 // Nobody set a custom style, so we just use a native scrollbar.
554 return ScrollView::createScrollbar(orientation);
555}

568}

570void FrameView::didDestroyRenderTree()
571{
572 ASSERT(!layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot());
573 ASSERT(m_widgetsInRenderTree.isEmpty());
574
575 // If the render tree is destroyed below FrameView::updateEmbeddedObjects(), there will still be a null sentinel in the set.
576 // Everything else should have removed itself as the tree was felled.
577 ASSERT(!m_embeddedObjectsToUpdate || m_embeddedObjectsToUpdate->isEmpty() || (m_embeddedObjectsToUpdate->size() == 1 && m_embeddedObjectsToUpdate->first() == nullptr));
578
579 ASSERT(!m_viewportConstrainedObjects || m_viewportConstrainedObjects->computesEmpty());
580 ASSERT(!m_slowRepaintObjects || m_slowRepaintObjects->computesEmpty());
581}

583void FrameView::setContentsSize(const IntSize& size)
584{
585 if (size == contentsSize())
586 return;
587
588 layoutContext().disableSetNeedsLayout();
589
590 ScrollView::setContentsSize(size);
591 contentsResized();
592
593 Page* page = frame().page();
594 if (!page)
595 return;
596
597 updateScrollableAreaSet();
598
599 page->chrome().contentsSizeChanged(frame(), size); // Notify only.
600
601 if (frame().isMainFrame()) {
602 page->pageOverlayController().didChangeDocumentSize();
603 BackForwardCache::singleton().markPagesForContentsSizeChanged(*page);
604 }
605 layoutContext().enableSetNeedsLayout();
606}
607
608void FrameView::adjustViewSize()
609{
610 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
611 if (!renderView)
612 return;
613
614 ASSERT(frame().view() == this);
615
616 const IntRect rect = renderView->documentRect();
617 const IntSize& size = rect.size();
618 ScrollView::setScrollOrigin(IntPoint(-rect.x(), -rect.y()), !frame().document()->printing(), size == contentsSize());
619
620 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Layout, stream << "FrameView " << this << " adjustViewSize: unscaled document rect changed to " << renderView->unscaledDocumentRect() << " (scaled to " << size << ")");
621
622 setContentsSize(size);
623}
624
625void FrameView::applyOverflowToViewport(const RenderElement& renderer, ScrollbarMode& hMode, ScrollbarMode& vMode)
626{
627 // Handle the overflow:hidden/scroll case for the body/html elements. WinIE treats
628 // overflow:hidden and overflow:scroll on <body> as applying to the document's
629 // scrollbars. The CSS2.1 draft states that HTML UAs should use the <html> or <body> element and XML/XHTML UAs should
630 // use the root element.
631
632 // To combat the inability to scroll on a page with overflow:hidden on the root when scaled, disregard hidden when
633 // there is a frameScaleFactor that is greater than one on the main frame. Also disregard hidden if there is a
634 // header or footer.
635
636 bool overrideHidden = frame().isMainFrame() && ((frame().frameScaleFactor() > 1) || headerHeight() || footerHeight());
637
638 Overflow overflowX = renderer.style().overflowX();
639 Overflow overflowY = renderer.style().overflowY();
640
641 if (is<RenderSVGRoot>(renderer)) {
642 // FIXME: evaluate if we can allow overflow for these cases too.
643 // Overflow is always hidden when stand-alone SVG documents are embedded.
644 if (downcast<RenderSVGRoot>(renderer).isEmbeddedThroughFrameContainingSVGDocument()) {
645 overflowX = Overflow::Hidden;
646 overflowY = Overflow::Hidden;
647 }
648 }
649
650 switch (overflowX) {
651 case Overflow::Hidden:
652 if (overrideHidden)
653 hMode = ScrollbarAuto;
654 else
655 hMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
656 break;
657 case Overflow::Scroll:
658 hMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOn;
659 break;
660 case Overflow::Auto:
661 hMode = ScrollbarAuto;
662 break;
663 default:
664 // Don't set it at all.
665 ;
666 }
667
668 switch (overflowY) {
669 case Overflow::Hidden:
670 if (overrideHidden)
671 vMode = ScrollbarAuto;
672 else
673 vMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
674 break;
675 case Overflow::Scroll:
676 vMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOn;
677 break;
678 case Overflow::Auto:
679 vMode = ScrollbarAuto;
680 break;
681 default:
682 // Don't set it at all. Values of Overflow::PagedX and Overflow::PagedY are handled by applyPaginationToViewPort().
683 ;
684 }
685}
686
687void FrameView::applyPaginationToViewport()
688{
689 auto* document = frame().document();
690 auto* documentElement = document ? document->documentElement() : nullptr;
691 if (!documentElement || !documentElement->renderer()) {
692 setPagination(Pagination());
693 return;
694 }
695
696 auto& documentRenderer = *documentElement->renderer();
697 auto* documentOrBodyRenderer = &documentRenderer;
698
699 auto* body = document->body();
700 if (body && body->renderer()) {
701 documentOrBodyRenderer = documentRenderer.style().overflowX() == Overflow::Visible && is<HTMLHtmlElement>(*documentElement) ?
702 body->renderer() : &documentRenderer;
703 }
704
705 Pagination pagination;
706 Overflow overflowY = documentOrBodyRenderer->style().overflowY();
707 if (overflowY == Overflow::PagedX || overflowY == Overflow::PagedY) {
708 pagination.mode = WebCore::paginationModeForRenderStyle(documentOrBodyRenderer->style());
709 GapLength columnGapLength = documentOrBodyRenderer->style().columnGap();
710 pagination.gap = 0;
711 if (!columnGapLength.isNormal()) {
712 if (auto* containerForPaginationGap = is<RenderBox>(documentOrBodyRenderer) ? downcast<RenderBox>(documentOrBodyRenderer) : documentOrBodyRenderer->containingBlock())
713 pagination.gap = valueForLength(columnGapLength.length(), containerForPaginationGap->availableLogicalWidth()).toUnsigned();
714 }
715 }
716 setPagination(pagination);
717}
718
719void FrameView::calculateScrollbarModesForLayout(ScrollbarMode& hMode, ScrollbarMode& vMode, ScrollbarModesCalculationStrategy strategy)
720{
721 m_viewportRendererType = ViewportRendererType::None;
722
723 const HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = frame().ownerElement();
724 if (owner && (owner->scrollingMode() == ScrollbarAlwaysOff)) {
725 hMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
726 vMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
727 return;
728 }
729
730 if (m_canHaveScrollbars || strategy == RulesFromWebContentOnly) {
731 hMode = ScrollbarAuto;
732 vMode = ScrollbarAuto;
733 } else {
734 hMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
735 vMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
736 }
737
738 if (layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot())
739 return;
740
741 auto* document = frame().document();
742 if (!document)
743 return;
744
745 auto* documentElement = document->documentElement();
746 if (!documentElement)
747 return;
748
749 auto* bodyOrFrameset = document->bodyOrFrameset();
750 auto* rootRenderer = documentElement->renderer();
751 if (!bodyOrFrameset || !bodyOrFrameset->renderer()) {
752 if (rootRenderer) {
753 applyOverflowToViewport(*rootRenderer, hMode, vMode);
754 m_viewportRendererType = ViewportRendererType::Document;
755 }
756 return;
757 }
758
759 if (is<HTMLFrameSetElement>(*bodyOrFrameset) && !frameFlatteningEnabled()) {
760 vMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
761 hMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
762 return;
763 }
764
765 if (is<HTMLBodyElement>(*bodyOrFrameset) && rootRenderer) {
766 // It's sufficient to just check the X overflow,
767 // since it's illegal to have visible in only one direction.
768 if (rootRenderer->style().overflowX() == Overflow::Visible && is<HTMLHtmlElement>(documentElement)) {
769 auto* bodyRenderer = bodyOrFrameset->renderer();
770 if (bodyRenderer) {
771 applyOverflowToViewport(*bodyRenderer, hMode, vMode);
772 m_viewportRendererType = ViewportRendererType::Body;
773 }
774 } else {
775 applyOverflowToViewport(*rootRenderer, hMode, vMode);
776 m_viewportRendererType = ViewportRendererType::Document;
777 }
778 }
779}

916
917void FrameView::updateSnapOffsets()
918{
919 if (!frame().document())
920 return;
921
922 auto& document = *frame().document();
923 auto* documentElement = document.documentElement();
924 RenderBox* bodyRenderer = document.bodyOrFrameset() ? document.bodyOrFrameset()->renderBox() : nullptr;
925 RenderBox* rootRenderer = documentElement ? documentElement->renderBox() : nullptr;
926 auto rendererSyleHasScrollSnap = [](const RenderObject* renderer) {
927 return renderer && renderer->style().scrollSnapType().strictness != ScrollSnapStrictness::None;
928 };
929
930 const RenderStyle* styleToUse = nullptr;
931 if (rendererSyleHasScrollSnap(bodyRenderer)) {
932 // The specification doesn't allow setting scroll-snap-type on the body, but
933 // we do this to ensure backwards compatibility with an earlier version of the
934 // specification: See webkit.org/b/200643.
935 styleToUse = &bodyRenderer->style();
936 } else if (rendererSyleHasScrollSnap(rootRenderer))
937 styleToUse = &rootRenderer->style();
938
939 if (!styleToUse || !documentElement) {
940 clearSnapOffsets();
941 return;
942 }
943
944 // updateSnapOffsetsForScrollableArea calculates scroll offsets with all rectangles having their origin at the
945 // padding box rectangle of the scrollable element. Unlike for overflow:scroll, the FrameView viewport includes
946 // the root element margins. This means that we need to offset the viewport rectangle to make it relative to
947 // the padding box of the root element.
948 LayoutRect viewport = LayoutRect(IntPoint(), baseLayoutViewportSize());
949 viewport.move(-rootRenderer->marginLeft(), -rootRenderer->marginTop());
950
951 updateSnapOffsetsForScrollableArea(*this, *rootRenderer, *styleToUse, viewport, rootRenderer->style().writingMode(), rootRenderer->style().direction());
952}
953
954bool FrameView::isScrollSnapInProgress() const
955{
956 if (scrollbarsSuppressed())
957 return false;
958
959 // If the scrolling thread updates the scroll position for this FrameView, then we should return
960 // ScrollingCoordinator::isScrollSnapInProgress().
961 if (auto scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator()) {
962 if (scrollingCoordinator->isScrollSnapInProgress(scrollingNodeID()))
963 return true;
964 }
965
966 // If the main thread updates the scroll position for this FrameView, we should return
967 // ScrollAnimator::isScrollSnapInProgress().
968 if (ScrollAnimator* scrollAnimator = existingScrollAnimator())
969 return scrollAnimator->isScrollSnapInProgress();
970
971 return false;
972}

975{
976 renderView()->compositor().updateScrollSnapPropertiesWithFrameView(*this);
977}
978
979bool FrameView::flushCompositingStateForThisFrame(const Frame& rootFrameForFlush)
980{
981#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
982 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().layoutFormattingContextEnabled()) {
983 if (auto* view = existingDisplayView())
984 view->flushLayers();
985 return true;
986 }
987#endif
988
989 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
990 if (!renderView)
991 return true; // We don't want to keep trying to update layers if we have no renderer.
992
993 ASSERT(frame().view() == this);
994
995 // If we sync compositing layers when a layout is pending, we may cause painting of compositing
996 // layer content to occur before layout has happened, which will cause paintContents() to bail.
997 if (needsLayout())
998 return false;
999
1000#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1001 if (LegacyTileCache* tileCache = legacyTileCache())
1002 tileCache->doPendingRepaints();
1003#endif
1004
1005 renderView->compositor().flushPendingLayerChanges(&rootFrameForFlush == m_frame.ptr());
1006
1007 return true;
1008}

1016GraphicsLayer* FrameView::graphicsLayerForPlatformWidget(PlatformWidget platformWidget)
1017{
1018 // To find the Widget that corresponds with platformWidget we have to do a linear
1019 // search of our child widgets.
1020 const Widget* foundWidget = nullptr;
1021 for (auto& widget : children()) {
1022 if (widget->platformWidget() != platformWidget)
1023 continue;
1024 foundWidget = widget.ptr();
1025 break;
1026 }
1027
1028 if (!foundWidget)
1029 return nullptr;
1030
1031 auto* renderWidget = RenderWidget::find(*foundWidget);
1032 if (!renderWidget)
1033 return nullptr;
1034
1035 auto* widgetLayer = renderWidget->layer();
1036 if (!widgetLayer || !widgetLayer->isComposited())
1037 return nullptr;
1038
1039 return widgetLayer->backing()->parentForSublayers();
1040}

1042LayoutRect FrameView::fixedScrollableAreaBoundsInflatedForScrolling(const LayoutRect& uninflatedBounds) const
1043{
1044 LayoutPoint scrollPosition;
1045 LayoutSize topLeftExpansion;
1046 LayoutSize bottomRightExpansion;
1047
1048 if (frame().settings().visualViewportEnabled()) {
1049 // FIXME: this is wrong under zooming; uninflatedBounds is scaled but the scroll positions are not.
1050 scrollPosition = layoutViewportRect().location();
1051 topLeftExpansion = scrollPosition - unscaledMinimumScrollPosition();
1052 bottomRightExpansion = unscaledMaximumScrollPosition() - scrollPosition;
1053 } else {
1054 scrollPosition = scrollPositionRespectingCustomFixedPosition();
1055 topLeftExpansion = scrollPosition - minimumScrollPosition();
1056 bottomRightExpansion = maximumScrollPosition() - scrollPosition;
1057 }
1058
1059 return LayoutRect(uninflatedBounds.location() - topLeftExpansion, uninflatedBounds.size() + topLeftExpansion + bottomRightExpansion);
1060}

1063{

1069 return scrollPositionForFixedPosition();

1169bool FrameView::flushCompositingStateIncludingSubframes()
1170{
1171 bool allFramesFlushed = flushCompositingStateForThisFrame(frame());
1172
1173 for (Frame* child = frame().tree().firstRenderedChild(); child; child = child->tree().traverseNextRendered(m_frame.ptr())) {
1174 if (!child->view())
1175 continue;
1176 bool flushed = child->view()->flushCompositingStateForThisFrame(frame());
1177 allFramesFlushed &= flushed;
1178 }
1179 return allFramesFlushed;

1199void FrameView::forceLayoutParentViewIfNeeded()
1200{
1201 RenderWidget* ownerRenderer = frame().ownerRenderer();
1202 if (!ownerRenderer)
1203 return;
1204
1205 RenderBox* contentBox = embeddedContentBox();
1206 if (!contentBox)
1207 return;
1208
1209 auto& svgRoot = downcast<RenderSVGRoot>(*contentBox);
1210 if (svgRoot.everHadLayout() && !svgRoot.needsLayout())
1211 return;
1212
1213 LOG(Layout, "FrameView %p forceLayoutParentViewIfNeeded scheduling layout on parent FrameView %p", this, &ownerRenderer->view().frameView());
1214
1215 // If the embedded SVG document appears the first time, the ownerRenderer has already finished
1216 // layout without knowing about the existence of the embedded SVG document, because RenderReplaced
1217 // embeddedContentBox() returns nullptr, as long as the embedded document isn't loaded yet. Before
1218 // bothering to lay out the SVG document, mark the ownerRenderer needing layout and ask its
1219 // FrameView for a layout. After that the RenderEmbeddedObject (ownerRenderer) carries the
1220 // correct size, which RenderSVGRoot::computeReplacedLogicalWidth/Height rely on, when laying
1221 // out for the first time, or when the RenderSVGRoot size has changed dynamically (eg. via <script>).
1222
1223 ownerRenderer->setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
1224 ownerRenderer->view().frameView().layoutContext().scheduleLayout();
1225}
1226
1227void FrameView::markRootOrBodyRendererDirty() const
1228{
1229 auto& document = *frame().document();
1230 RenderBox* rootRenderer = document.documentElement() ? document.documentElement()->renderBox() : nullptr;
1231 auto* body = document.bodyOrFrameset();
1232 RenderBox* bodyRenderer = rootRenderer && body ? body->renderBox() : nullptr;
1233 if (bodyRenderer && bodyRenderer->stretchesToViewport())
1234 bodyRenderer->setChildNeedsLayout();
1235 else if (rootRenderer && rootRenderer->stretchesToViewport())
1236 rootRenderer->setChildNeedsLayout();
1237}
1238
1239void FrameView::adjustScrollbarsForLayout(bool isFirstLayout)
1240{
1241 ScrollbarMode hMode;
1242 ScrollbarMode vMode;
1243 calculateScrollbarModesForLayout(hMode, vMode);
1244 if (isFirstLayout && !layoutContext().isLayoutNested()) {
1245 setScrollbarsSuppressed(true);
1246 // Set the initial vMode to AlwaysOn if we're auto.
1247 if (vMode == ScrollbarAuto)
1248 setVerticalScrollbarMode(ScrollbarAlwaysOn); // This causes a vertical scrollbar to appear.
1249 // Set the initial hMode to AlwaysOff if we're auto.
1250 if (hMode == ScrollbarAuto)
1251 setHorizontalScrollbarMode(ScrollbarAlwaysOff); // This causes a horizontal scrollbar to disappear.
1252 ASSERT(frame().page());
1253 if (frame().page()->isMonitoringWheelEvents())
1254 scrollAnimator().setWheelEventTestMonitor(frame().page()->wheelEventTestMonitor());
1255 setScrollbarModes(hMode, vMode);
1256 setScrollbarsSuppressed(false, true);
1257 } else if (hMode != horizontalScrollbarMode() || vMode != verticalScrollbarMode())
1258 setScrollbarModes(hMode, vMode);
1259}
1260
1261void FrameView::willDoLayout(WeakPtr<RenderElement> layoutRoot)
1262{
1263 bool subtreeLayout = !is<RenderView>(*layoutRoot);
1264 if (subtreeLayout)
1265 return;
1266
1267 if (auto* body = frame().document()->bodyOrFrameset()) {
1268 if (is<HTMLFrameSetElement>(*body) && !frameFlatteningEnabled() && body->renderer())
1269 body->renderer()->setChildNeedsLayout();
1270 }
1271 auto firstLayout = !layoutContext().didFirstLayout();
1272 if (firstLayout) {
1273 m_lastViewportSize = sizeForResizeEvent();
1274 m_lastZoomFactor = layoutRoot->style().zoom();
1275 m_firstLayoutCallbackPending = true;
1276 }
1277 adjustScrollbarsForLayout(firstLayout);
1278
1279 auto oldSize = m_size;
1280 LayoutSize newSize = layoutSize();
1281 if (oldSize != newSize) {
1282 m_size = newSize;
1283 LOG(Layout, " layout size changed from %.3fx%.3f to %.3fx%.3f", oldSize.width().toFloat(), oldSize.height().toFloat(), newSize.width().toFloat(), newSize.height().toFloat());
1284 layoutContext().setNeedsFullRepaint();
1285 if (!firstLayout)
1286 markRootOrBodyRendererDirty();
1287 }
1288 forceLayoutParentViewIfNeeded();
1289}
1290
1291void FrameView::didLayout(WeakPtr<RenderElement> layoutRoot)
1292{
1293 renderView()->releaseProtectedRenderWidgets();
1294 auto* layoutRootEnclosingLayer = layoutRoot->enclosingLayer();
1295 layoutRootEnclosingLayer->updateLayerPositionsAfterLayout(!is<RenderView>(*layoutRoot), layoutContext().needsFullRepaint());
1296
1297 updateCompositingLayersAfterLayout();
1298
1299 auto document = makeRef(*frame().document());
1300
1301#if PLATFORM(COCOA) || PLATFORM(WIN) || PLATFORM(GTK)
1302 if (auto* cache = document->existingAXObjectCache())
1303 cache->postNotification(layoutRoot.get(), AXObjectCache::AXLayoutComplete);
1304#endif
1305
1306 frame().invalidateContentEventRegionsIfNeeded(Frame::InvalidateContentEventRegionsReason::Layout);
1307 document->invalidateRenderingDependentRegions();
1308
1309 updateCanBlitOnScrollRecursively();
1310
1311 handleDeferredScrollUpdateAfterContentSizeChange();
1312
1313 handleDeferredScrollbarsUpdate();
1314 handleDeferredPositionScrollbarLayers();
1315
1316 if (document->hasListenerType(Document::OVERFLOWCHANGED_LISTENER))
1317 updateOverflowStatus(layoutWidth() < contentsWidth(), layoutHeight() < contentsHeight());
1318
1319 document->markers().invalidateRectsForAllMarkers();
1320}

1323{
1324 return (layoutContext().layoutPhase() < FrameViewLayoutContext::LayoutPhase::InPostLayout) && (layoutContext().layoutPhase() != FrameViewLayoutContext::LayoutPhase::OutsideLayout);
1325}

1389
1390bool FrameView::useSlowRepaints(bool considerOverlap) const
1391{
1392 bool mustBeSlow = hasSlowRepaintObjects() || (platformWidget() && hasViewportConstrainedObjects());
1393
1394 // FIXME: WidgetMac.mm makes the assumption that useSlowRepaints ==
1395 // m_contentIsOpaque, so don't take the fast path for composited layers
1396 // if they are a platform widget in order to get painting correctness
1397 // for transparent layers. See the comment in WidgetMac::paint.
1398 if (usesCompositedScrolling() && !platformWidget())
1399 return mustBeSlow;
1400
1401 bool isOverlapped = m_isOverlapped && considerOverlap;
1402
1403 if (mustBeSlow || m_cannotBlitToWindow || isOverlapped || !m_contentIsOpaque)
1404 return true;
1405
1406 if (FrameView* parentView = parentFrameView())
1407 return parentView->useSlowRepaints(considerOverlap);
1408
1409 return false;
1410}
1411
1412bool FrameView::useSlowRepaintsIfNotOverlapped() const
1413{

1418{

1421 view->setCanBlitOnScroll(!view->useSlowRepaints());

1506void FrameView::addSlowRepaintObject(RenderElement& renderer)
1507{
1508 bool hadSlowRepaintObjects = hasSlowRepaintObjects();
1509
1510 if (!m_slowRepaintObjects)
1511 m_slowRepaintObjects = makeUnique<WeakHashSet<RenderElement>>();
1512
1513 auto addResult = m_slowRepaintObjects->add(renderer);
1514 if (addResult.isNewEntry) {
1515 if (auto layer = renderer.enclosingLayer())
1516 layer->setNeedsScrollingTreeUpdate();
1517 }
1518
1519 if (hadSlowRepaintObjects)
1520 return;
1521
1522 updateCanBlitOnScrollRecursively();
1523}
1524
1525void FrameView::removeSlowRepaintObject(RenderElement& renderer)
1526{
1527 if (!m_slowRepaintObjects)
1528 return;
1529
1530 bool removed = m_slowRepaintObjects->remove(renderer);
1531 if (removed) {
1532 if (auto layer = renderer.enclosingLayer())
1533 layer->setNeedsScrollingTreeUpdate();
1534 }
1535
1536 if (!m_slowRepaintObjects->computesEmpty())
1537 return;
1538
1539 m_slowRepaintObjects = nullptr;
1540 updateCanBlitOnScrollRecursively();
1541}

1543void FrameView::addViewportConstrainedObject(RenderLayerModelObject& object)
1544{
1545 if (!m_viewportConstrainedObjects)
1546 m_viewportConstrainedObjects = makeUnique<WeakHashSet<RenderLayerModelObject>>();
1547
1548 if (!m_viewportConstrainedObjects->contains(object)) {
1549 m_viewportConstrainedObjects->add(object);
1550 if (platformWidget())
1551 updateCanBlitOnScrollRecursively();
1552
1553 if (auto scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator())
1554 scrollingCoordinator->frameViewFixedObjectsDidChange(*this);
1555 }
1556}

1558void FrameView::removeViewportConstrainedObject(RenderLayerModelObject& object)
1559{
1560 if (m_viewportConstrainedObjects && m_viewportConstrainedObjects->remove(object)) {
1561 if (auto scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator())
1562 scrollingCoordinator->frameViewFixedObjectsDidChange(*this);
1563
1564 // FIXME: In addFixedObject() we only call this if there's a platform widget,
1565 // why isn't the same check being made here?
1566 updateCanBlitOnScrollRecursively();
1567 }

1570LayoutSize FrameView::expandedLayoutViewportSize(const LayoutSize& baseLayoutViewportSize, const LayoutSize& documentSize, double heightExpansionFactor)
1571{
1572 if (!heightExpansionFactor)
1573 return baseLayoutViewportSize;
1574
1575 auto documentHeight = documentSize.height();
1576 auto layoutViewportHeight = baseLayoutViewportSize.height();
1577 if (layoutViewportHeight > documentHeight)
1578 return baseLayoutViewportSize;
1579
1580 return { baseLayoutViewportSize.width(), std::min(documentHeight, LayoutUnit((1 + heightExpansionFactor) * layoutViewportHeight)) };
1581}
1582
1583LayoutRect FrameView::computeUpdatedLayoutViewportRect(const LayoutRect& layoutViewport, const LayoutRect& documentRect, const LayoutSize& unobscuredContentSize, const LayoutRect& unobscuredContentRect, const LayoutSize& baseLayoutViewportSize, const LayoutPoint& stableLayoutViewportOriginMin, const LayoutPoint& stableLayoutViewportOriginMax, LayoutViewportConstraint constraint)
1584{
1585 LayoutRect layoutViewportRect = layoutViewport;
1586
1587 // The layout viewport is never smaller than baseLayoutViewportSize, and never be smaller than the unobscuredContentRect.
1588 LayoutSize constrainedSize = baseLayoutViewportSize;
1589 layoutViewportRect.setSize(constrainedSize.expandedTo(unobscuredContentSize));
1590
1591 LayoutPoint layoutViewportOrigin = computeLayoutViewportOrigin(unobscuredContentRect, stableLayoutViewportOriginMin, stableLayoutViewportOriginMax, layoutViewportRect, StickToViewportBounds);
1592
1593 // FIXME: Is this equivalent to calling computeLayoutViewportOrigin() with StickToDocumentBounds?
1594 if (constraint == LayoutViewportConstraint::ConstrainedToDocumentRect) {
1595 // The max stable layout viewport origin really depends on the size of the layout viewport itself, so we need to adjust the location of the layout viewport one final time to make sure it does not end up out of bounds of the document.
1596 // Without this adjustment (and with using the non-constrained unobscuredContentRect's size as the size of the layout viewport) the layout viewport can be pushed past the bounds of the document during rubber-banding, and cannot be pushed
1597 // back in until the user scrolls back in the other direction.
1598 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(clampTo<float>(layoutViewportOrigin.x().toFloat(), 0, documentRect.width() - layoutViewportRect.width()));
1599 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(clampTo<float>(layoutViewportOrigin.y().toFloat(), 0, documentRect.height() - layoutViewportRect.height()));
1600 }
1601 layoutViewportRect.setLocation(layoutViewportOrigin);
1602
1603 return layoutViewportRect;
1604}
1605
1606// visualViewport and layoutViewport are both in content coordinates (unzoomed).
1607LayoutPoint FrameView::computeLayoutViewportOrigin(const LayoutRect& visualViewport, const LayoutPoint& stableLayoutViewportOriginMin, const LayoutPoint& stableLayoutViewportOriginMax, const LayoutRect& layoutViewport, ScrollBehaviorForFixedElements fixedBehavior)
1608{
1609 LayoutPoint layoutViewportOrigin = layoutViewport.location();
1610 bool allowRubberBanding = fixedBehavior == StickToViewportBounds;
1611
1612 if (visualViewport.width() > layoutViewport.width()) {
1613 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(visualViewport.x());
1614 if (!allowRubberBanding) {
1615 if (layoutViewportOrigin.x() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.x())
1616 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.x());
1617 else if (layoutViewportOrigin.x() > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.x())
1618 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.x());
1619 }
1620 } else {
1621 bool rubberbandingAtLeft = allowRubberBanding && visualViewport.x() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.x();
1622 bool rubberbandingAtRight = allowRubberBanding && (visualViewport.maxX() - layoutViewport.width()) > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.x();
1623
1624 if (visualViewport.x() < layoutViewport.x() || rubberbandingAtLeft)
1625 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(visualViewport.x());
1626
1627 if (visualViewport.maxX() > layoutViewport.maxX() || rubberbandingAtRight)
1628 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(visualViewport.maxX() - layoutViewport.width());
1629
1630 if (!rubberbandingAtLeft && layoutViewportOrigin.x() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.x())
1631 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.x());
1632
1633 if (!rubberbandingAtRight && layoutViewportOrigin.x() > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.x())
1634 layoutViewportOrigin.setX(stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.x());
1635 }
1636
1637 if (visualViewport.height() > layoutViewport.height()) {
1638 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(visualViewport.y());
1639 if (!allowRubberBanding) {
1640 if (layoutViewportOrigin.y() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.y())
1641 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.y());
1642 else if (layoutViewportOrigin.y() > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.y())
1643 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.y());
1644 }
1645 } else {
1646 bool rubberbandingAtTop = allowRubberBanding && visualViewport.y() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.y();
1647 bool rubberbandingAtBottom = allowRubberBanding && (visualViewport.maxY() - layoutViewport.height()) > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.y();
1648
1649 if (visualViewport.y() < layoutViewport.y() || rubberbandingAtTop)
1650 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(visualViewport.y());
1651
1652 if (visualViewport.maxY() > layoutViewport.maxY() || rubberbandingAtBottom)
1653 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(visualViewport.maxY() - layoutViewport.height());
1654
1655 if (!rubberbandingAtTop && layoutViewportOrigin.y() < stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.y())
1656 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(stableLayoutViewportOriginMin.y());
1657
1658 if (!rubberbandingAtBottom && layoutViewportOrigin.y() > stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.y())
1659 layoutViewportOrigin.setY(stableLayoutViewportOriginMax.y());
1660 }
1661
1662 return layoutViewportOrigin;
1663}

1665void FrameView::setBaseLayoutViewportOrigin(LayoutPoint origin, TriggerLayoutOrNot layoutTriggering)
1666{
1667 ASSERT(frame().settings().visualViewportEnabled());
1668
1669 if (origin == m_layoutViewportOrigin)
1670 return;
1671
1672 m_layoutViewportOrigin = origin;
1673 if (layoutTriggering == TriggerLayoutOrNot::Yes)
1674 setViewportConstrainedObjectsNeedLayout();
1675
1676 if (TiledBacking* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking()) {
1677 FloatRect layoutViewport = layoutViewportRect();
1678 layoutViewport.moveBy(unscaledScrollOrigin()); // tiledBacking deals in top-left relative coordinates.
1679 tiledBacking->setLayoutViewportRect(layoutViewport);
1680 }
1681}
1682
1683void FrameView::setLayoutViewportOverrideRect(std::optional<LayoutRect> rect, TriggerLayoutOrNot layoutTriggering)
1684{
1685 if (rect == m_layoutViewportOverrideRect)
1686 return;
1687
1688 LayoutRect oldRect = layoutViewportRect();
1689 m_layoutViewportOverrideRect = rect;
1690
1691 // Triggering layout on height changes is necessary to make bottom-fixed elements behave correctly.
1692 if (oldRect.height() != layoutViewportRect().height())
1693 layoutTriggering = TriggerLayoutOrNot::Yes;
1694
1695 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "\nFrameView " << this << " setLayoutViewportOverrideRect() - changing override layout viewport from " << oldRect << " to " << m_layoutViewportOverrideRect.value_or(LayoutRect()) << " layoutTriggering " << (layoutTriggering == TriggerLayoutOrNot::Yes ? "yes" : "no"));
1696
1697 if (oldRect != layoutViewportRect() && layoutTriggering == TriggerLayoutOrNot::Yes)
1698 setViewportConstrainedObjectsNeedLayout();
1699}

1706LayoutSize FrameView::baseLayoutViewportSize() const
1707{
1708 return renderView() ? renderView()->size() : size();
1709}
1710
1711void FrameView::updateLayoutViewport()
1712{
1713 if (!frame().settings().visualViewportEnabled())
1714 return;
1715
1716 // Don't update the layout viewport if we're in the middle of adjusting scrollbars. We'll get another call
1717 // as a post-layout task.
1718 if (layoutContext().layoutPhase() == FrameViewLayoutContext::LayoutPhase::InViewSizeAdjust)
1719 return;
1720
1721 LayoutRect layoutViewport = layoutViewportRect();
1722
1723 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "\nFrameView " << this << " updateLayoutViewport() totalContentSize " << totalContentsSize() << " unscaledDocumentRect " << (renderView() ? renderView()->unscaledDocumentRect() : IntRect()) << " header height " << headerHeight() << " footer height " << footerHeight() << " fixed behavior " << scrollBehaviorForFixedElements());
1724 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "layoutViewport: " << layoutViewport);
1725 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "visualViewport: " << visualViewportRect() << " (is override " << (bool)m_visualViewportOverrideRect << ")");
1726 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "stable origins: min: " << minStableLayoutViewportOrigin() << " max: "<< maxStableLayoutViewportOrigin());
1727
1728 if (m_layoutViewportOverrideRect) {
1729 if (currentScrollType() == ScrollType::Programmatic) {
1730 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "computing new override layout viewport because of programmatic scrolling");
1731 LayoutPoint newOrigin = computeLayoutViewportOrigin(visualViewportRect(), minStableLayoutViewportOrigin(), maxStableLayoutViewportOrigin(), layoutViewport, StickToDocumentBounds);
1732 setLayoutViewportOverrideRect(LayoutRect(newOrigin, m_layoutViewportOverrideRect.value().size()));
1733 }
1734 layoutOrVisualViewportChanged();
1735 return;
1736 }
1737
1738 LayoutPoint newLayoutViewportOrigin = computeLayoutViewportOrigin(visualViewportRect(), minStableLayoutViewportOrigin(), maxStableLayoutViewportOrigin(), layoutViewport, scrollBehaviorForFixedElements());
1739 if (newLayoutViewportOrigin != m_layoutViewportOrigin) {
1740 setBaseLayoutViewportOrigin(newLayoutViewportOrigin);
1741 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "layoutViewport changed to " << layoutViewportRect());
1742 }
1743 layoutOrVisualViewportChanged();
1744}
1745
1746LayoutPoint FrameView::minStableLayoutViewportOrigin() const
1747{
1748 return unscaledMinimumScrollPosition();
1749}
1750
1751LayoutPoint FrameView::maxStableLayoutViewportOrigin() const
1752{
1753 LayoutPoint maxPosition = unscaledMaximumScrollPosition();
1754 maxPosition = (maxPosition - LayoutSize(0, headerHeight() + footerHeight())).expandedTo({ });
1755 return maxPosition;
1756}

1758IntPoint FrameView::unscaledScrollOrigin() const
1759{
1760 if (RenderView* renderView = this->renderView())
1761 return -renderView->unscaledDocumentRect().location(); // Akin to code in adjustViewSize().
1762
1763 return { };
1764}
1765
1766LayoutRect FrameView::layoutViewportRect() const
1767{
1768 if (m_layoutViewportOverrideRect)
1769 return m_layoutViewportOverrideRect.value();
1770
1771 // Size of initial containing block, anchored at scroll position, in document coordinates (unchanged by scale factor).
1772 return LayoutRect(m_layoutViewportOrigin, baseLayoutViewportSize());
1773}
1774
1775// visibleContentRect is in the bounds of the scroll view content. That consists of an
1776// optional header, the document, and an optional footer. Only the document is scaled,
1777// so we have to compute the visible part of the document in unscaled document coordinates.
1778// On iOS, pageScaleFactor is always 1 here, and we never have headers and footers.
1779LayoutRect FrameView::visibleDocumentRect(const FloatRect& visibleContentRect, float headerHeight, float footerHeight, const FloatSize& totalContentsSize, float pageScaleFactor)
1780{
1781 float contentsHeight = totalContentsSize.height() - headerHeight - footerHeight;
1782
1783 float rubberBandTop = std::min<float>(visibleContentRect.y(), 0);
1784 float visibleScaledDocumentTop = std::max<float>(visibleContentRect.y() - headerHeight, 0) + rubberBandTop;
1785
1786 float rubberBandBottom = std::min<float>((totalContentsSize.height() - visibleContentRect.y()) - visibleContentRect.height(), 0);
1787 float visibleScaledDocumentBottom = std::min<float>(visibleContentRect.maxY() - headerHeight, contentsHeight) - rubberBandBottom;
1788
1789 FloatRect visibleDocumentRect = visibleContentRect;
1790 visibleDocumentRect.setY(visibleScaledDocumentTop);
1791 visibleDocumentRect.setHeight(std::max<float>(visibleScaledDocumentBottom - visibleScaledDocumentTop, 0));
1792 visibleDocumentRect.scale(1 / pageScaleFactor);
1793
1794 return LayoutRect(visibleDocumentRect);
1795}
1796
1797LayoutRect FrameView::visualViewportRect() const
1798{
1799 if (m_visualViewportOverrideRect)
1800 return m_visualViewportOverrideRect.value();
1801
1802 FloatRect visibleContentRect = this->visibleContentRect(LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect);
1803 return visibleDocumentRect(visibleContentRect, headerHeight(), footerHeight(), totalContentsSize(), frameScaleFactor());
1804}

1840
1841LayoutPoint FrameView::scrollPositionForFixedPosition(const LayoutRect& visibleContentRect, const LayoutSize& totalContentsSize, const LayoutPoint& scrollPosition, const LayoutPoint& scrollOrigin, float frameScaleFactor, bool fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame, ScrollBehaviorForFixedElements behaviorForFixed, int headerHeight, int footerHeight)
1842{
1843 LayoutPoint position;
1844 if (behaviorForFixed == StickToDocumentBounds)
1845 position = ScrollableArea::constrainScrollPositionForOverhang(visibleContentRect, totalContentsSize, scrollPosition, scrollOrigin, headerHeight, footerHeight);
1846 else {
1847 position = scrollPosition;
1848 position.setY(position.y() - headerHeight);
1849 }
1850
1851 LayoutSize maxSize = totalContentsSize - visibleContentRect.size();
1852
1853 float dragFactorX = (fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame || !maxSize.width()) ? 1 : (totalContentsSize.width() - visibleContentRect.width() * frameScaleFactor) / maxSize.width();
1854 float dragFactorY = (fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame || !maxSize.height()) ? 1 : (totalContentsSize.height() - visibleContentRect.height() * frameScaleFactor) / maxSize.height();
1855
1856 return LayoutPoint(position.x() * dragFactorX / frameScaleFactor, position.y() * dragFactorY / frameScaleFactor);
1857}

1859float FrameView::yPositionForInsetClipLayer(const FloatPoint& scrollPosition, float topContentInset)
1860{
1861 if (!topContentInset)
1862 return 0;
1863
1864 // The insetClipLayer should not move for negative scroll values.
1865 float scrollY = std::max<float>(0, scrollPosition.y());
1866
1867 if (scrollY >= topContentInset)
1868 return 0;
1869
1870 return topContentInset - scrollY;
1871}

1874{
1875 if (!topContentInset)
1876 return 0;
1877
1878 float scrollY = std::max<float>(0, scrollPosition.y());
1879
1880 if (scrollY >= topContentInset)
1881 return topContentInset;
1882
1883 return scrollY;
1884}

1901#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1902LayoutRect FrameView::rectForViewportConstrainedObjects(const LayoutRect& visibleContentRect, const LayoutSize& totalContentsSize, float frameScaleFactor, bool fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame, ScrollBehaviorForFixedElements scrollBehavior)
1903{
1904 if (fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame)
1905 return visibleContentRect;
1906
1907 if (totalContentsSize.isEmpty())
1908 return visibleContentRect;
1909
1910 // We impose an lower limit on the size (so an upper limit on the scale) of
1911 // the rect used to position fixed objects so that they don't crowd into the
1912 // center of the screen at larger scales.
1913 const LayoutUnit maxContentWidthForZoomThreshold = 1024_lu;
1914 float zoomedOutScale = frameScaleFactor * visibleContentRect.width() / std::min(maxContentWidthForZoomThreshold, totalContentsSize.width());
1915 float constraintThresholdScale = 1.5 * zoomedOutScale;
1916 float maxPostionedObjectsRectScale = std::min(frameScaleFactor, constraintThresholdScale);
1917
1918 LayoutRect viewportConstrainedObjectsRect = visibleContentRect;
1919
1920 if (frameScaleFactor > constraintThresholdScale) {
1921 FloatRect contentRect(FloatPoint(), totalContentsSize);
1922 FloatRect viewportRect = visibleContentRect;
1923
1924 // Scale the rect up from a point that is relative to its position in the viewport.
1925 FloatSize sizeDelta = contentRect.size() - viewportRect.size();
1926
1927 FloatPoint scaleOrigin;
1928 scaleOrigin.setX(contentRect.x() + sizeDelta.width() > 0 ? contentRect.width() * (viewportRect.x() - contentRect.x()) / sizeDelta.width() : 0);
1929 scaleOrigin.setY(contentRect.y() + sizeDelta.height() > 0 ? contentRect.height() * (viewportRect.y() - contentRect.y()) / sizeDelta.height() : 0);
1930
1931 AffineTransform rescaleTransform = AffineTransform::translation(scaleOrigin.x(), scaleOrigin.y());
1932 rescaleTransform.scale(frameScaleFactor / maxPostionedObjectsRectScale, frameScaleFactor / maxPostionedObjectsRectScale);
1933 rescaleTransform = CGAffineTransformTranslate(rescaleTransform, -scaleOrigin.x(), -scaleOrigin.y());
1934
1935 viewportConstrainedObjectsRect = enclosingLayoutRect(rescaleTransform.mapRect(visibleContentRect));
1936 }
1937
1938 if (scrollBehavior == StickToDocumentBounds) {
1939 LayoutRect documentBounds(LayoutPoint(), totalContentsSize);
1940 viewportConstrainedObjectsRect.intersect(documentBounds);
1941 }
1942
1943 return viewportConstrainedObjectsRect;
1944}
1945
1946LayoutRect FrameView::viewportConstrainedObjectsRect() const
1947{
1948 return rectForViewportConstrainedObjects(visibleContentRect(), totalContentsSize(), frame().frameScaleFactor(), fixedElementsLayoutRelativeToFrame(), scrollBehaviorForFixedElements());
1949}
1950#endif

2002void FrameView::viewportContentsChanged()
2003{
2004 if (!frame().view()) {
2005 // The frame is being destroyed.
2006 return;
2007 }
2008
2009 if (auto* page = frame().page())
2010 page->updateValidationBubbleStateIfNeeded();

2013 // check if we should resume animated images or unthrottle DOM timers.
2014 applyRecursivelyWithVisibleRect([] (FrameView& frameView, const IntRect& visibleRect) {

2018 if (auto* renderView = frameView.frame().contentRenderer())
2019 renderView->updateVisibleViewportRect(visibleRect);
2020 });
2021}

2093bool FrameView::scrollContentsFastPath(const IntSize& scrollDelta, const IntRect& rectToScroll, const IntRect& clipRect)
2094{
2095 if (!m_viewportConstrainedObjects || m_viewportConstrainedObjects->computesEmpty()) {
2096 frame().page()->chrome().scroll(scrollDelta, rectToScroll, clipRect);
2097 return true;
2098 }
2099
2100 bool isCompositedContentLayer = usesCompositedScrolling();
2101
2102 // Get the rects of the fixed objects visible in the rectToScroll
2103 Region regionToUpdate;
2104 for (auto& renderer : *m_viewportConstrainedObjects) {
2105 if (!renderer.style().hasViewportConstrainedPosition())
2106 continue;
2107 if (renderer.isComposited())
2108 continue;
2109
2110 // Fixed items should always have layers.
2111 ASSERT(renderer.hasLayer());
2112 RenderLayer* layer = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(renderer).layer();
2113
2114 if (layer->viewportConstrainedNotCompositedReason() == RenderLayer::NotCompositedForBoundsOutOfView
2115 || layer->viewportConstrainedNotCompositedReason() == RenderLayer::NotCompositedForNoVisibleContent) {
2116 // Don't invalidate for invisible fixed layers.
2117 continue;
2118 }
2119
2120 if (layer->hasAncestorWithFilterOutsets()) {
2121 // If the fixed layer has a blur/drop-shadow filter applied on at least one of its parents, we cannot
2122 // scroll using the fast path, otherwise the outsets of the filter will be moved around the page.
2123 return false;
2124 }
2125
2126 // FIXME: use pixel snapping instead of enclosing when ScrollView has finished transitioning from IntRect to Float/LayoutRect.
2127 IntRect updateRect = enclosingIntRect(layer->repaintRectIncludingNonCompositingDescendants());
2128 updateRect = contentsToRootView(updateRect);
2129 if (!isCompositedContentLayer)
2130 updateRect.intersect(rectToScroll);
2131 if (!updateRect.isEmpty())
2132 regionToUpdate.unite(updateRect);
2133 }
2134
2135 // 1) scroll
2136 frame().page()->chrome().scroll(scrollDelta, rectToScroll, clipRect);
2137
2138 // 2) update the area of fixed objects that has been invalidated
2139 for (auto& updateRect : regionToUpdate.rects()) {
2140 IntRect scrolledRect = updateRect;
2141 scrolledRect.move(scrollDelta);
2142 updateRect.unite(scrolledRect);
2143 if (isCompositedContentLayer) {
2144 updateRect = rootViewToContents(updateRect);
2145 ASSERT(renderView());
2146 renderView()->layer()->setBackingNeedsRepaintInRect(updateRect);
2147 continue;
2148 }
2149 updateRect.intersect(rectToScroll);
2150 frame().page()->chrome().invalidateContentsAndRootView(updateRect);
2151 }
2152
2153 return true;
2154}
2155
2156void FrameView::scrollContentsSlowPath(const IntRect& updateRect)
2157{
2158 repaintSlowRepaintObjects();
2159
2160 if (!usesCompositedScrolling() && isEnclosedInCompositingLayer()) {
2161 if (RenderWidget* frameRenderer = frame().ownerRenderer()) {
2162 LayoutRect rect(frameRenderer->borderLeft() + frameRenderer->paddingLeft(), frameRenderer->borderTop() + frameRenderer->paddingTop(),
2163 visibleWidth(), visibleHeight());
2164 frameRenderer->repaintRectangle(rect);
2165 return;
2166 }
2167 }
2168
2169 ScrollView::scrollContentsSlowPath(updateRect);
2170}

2207bool FrameView::scrollToFragment(const URL& url)
2208{
2209 auto fragmentIdentifier = url.fragmentIdentifier();
2210 if (scrollToFragmentInternal(fragmentIdentifier))
2211 return true;
2212
2213 if (scrollToFragmentInternal(decodeURLEscapeSequences(fragmentIdentifier)))
2214 return true;
2215
2216 resetScrollAnchor();

2218}
2219
2220bool FrameView::scrollToFragmentInternal(StringView fragmentIdentifier)
2221{
2222 // If our URL has no ref, then we have no place we need to jump to.
2223 if (fragmentIdentifier.isNull())
2224 return false;
2225
2226 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << *this << " scrollToFragmentInternal " << fragmentIdentifier);
2227
2228 ASSERT(frame().document());
2229 auto& document = *frame().document();
2230 RELEASE_ASSERT(document.haveStylesheetsLoaded());
2231
2232 auto anchorElement = makeRefPtr(document.findAnchor(fragmentIdentifier));
2233
2234 LOG(Scrolling, " anchorElement is %p", anchorElement.get());
2235
2236 // Setting to null will clear the current target.
2237 document.setCSSTarget(anchorElement.get());
2238
2239 if (is<SVGDocument>(document)) {
2240 if (fragmentIdentifier.isEmpty())
2241 return false;
2242 if (auto rootElement = DocumentSVG::rootElement(document)) {
2243 if (rootElement->scrollToFragment(fragmentIdentifier))
2244 return true;
2245 // If SVG failed to scrollToAnchor() and anchorElement is null, no other scrolling will be possible.
2246 if (!anchorElement)
2247 return false;
2248 }
2249 } else if (!anchorElement && !(fragmentIdentifier.isEmpty() || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(fragmentIdentifier, "top"))) {
2250 // Implement the rule that "" and "top" both mean top of page as in other browsers.
2251 return false;
2252 }
2253
2254 RefPtr<ContainerNode> scrollPositionAnchor = anchorElement;
2255 if (!scrollPositionAnchor)
2256 scrollPositionAnchor = frame().document();
2257 maintainScrollPositionAtAnchor(scrollPositionAnchor.get());
2258
2259 // If the anchor accepts keyboard focus, move focus there to aid users relying on keyboard navigation.
2260 if (anchorElement) {
2261 if (anchorElement->isFocusable())
2262 document.setFocusedElement(anchorElement.get(), { { }, { }, { }, { }, FocusVisibility::Visible });
2263 else {
2264 document.setFocusedElement(nullptr);
2265 document.setFocusNavigationStartingNode(anchorElement.get());
2266 }
2267 }
2268
2269 return true;
2270}
2271
2272void FrameView::maintainScrollPositionAtAnchor(ContainerNode* anchorNode)
2273{
2274 LOG(Scrolling, "FrameView::maintainScrollPositionAtAnchor at %p", anchorNode);
2275
2276 m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor = anchorNode;
2277 if (!m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor)
2278 return;
2279 m_shouldScrollToFocusedElement = false;
2280 m_delayedScrollToFocusedElementTimer.stop();
2281
2282 // We need to update the layout before scrolling, otherwise we could
2283 // really mess things up if an anchor scroll comes at a bad moment.
2284 frame().document()->updateStyleIfNeeded();
2285 // Only do a layout if changes have occurred that make it necessary.
2286 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
2287 if (renderView && renderView->needsLayout())
2288 layoutContext().layout();
2289 else
2290 scrollToAnchor();
2291}

2299 bounds = renderer->absoluteAnchorRect();
2300 int centeringOffsetX = (rect.width() - bounds.width()) / 2;

2302 setScrollPosition(IntPoint(bounds.x() - centeringOffsetX - rect.x(), bounds.y() - centeringOffsetY - rect.y()));

2306{
2307 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "FrameView::setScrollPosition " << scrollPosition << " , clearing anchor");
2308

2310 setCurrentScrollType(options.type);
2311

2321
2322 if (options.animated == AnimatedScroll::Yes)
2323 scrollToPositionWithAnimation(snappedPosition, currentScrollType(), options.clamping);

2381 if (!document)
2382 return;

2401 LayoutRect absoluteBounds = renderer->absoluteAnchorRect(&insideFixed);
2402 renderer->scrollRectToVisible(absoluteBounds, insideFixed, { m_selectionRevealModeForFocusedElement, ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignCenterIfNeeded, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });

2500 Page* page = frame().page();

2547void FrameView::updateScriptedAnimationsAndTimersThrottlingState(const IntRect& visibleRect)
2548{
2549 if (frame().isMainFrame())
2550 return;
2551
2552 auto* document = frame().document();
2553 if (!document)
2554 return;
2555
2556 // We don't throttle zero-size or display:none frames because those are usually utility frames.
2557 bool shouldThrottle = visibleRect.isEmpty() && !m_size.isEmpty() && frame().ownerRenderer();
2558 document->setTimerThrottlingEnabled(shouldThrottle);
2559
2560 auto* page = frame().page();
2561 if (!page || !page->canUpdateThrottlingReason(ThrottlingReason::OutsideViewport))
2562 return;
2563
2564 auto* scriptedAnimationController = document->scriptedAnimationController();
2565 if (!scriptedAnimationController)
2566 return;
2567
2568 if (shouldThrottle)
2569 scriptedAnimationController->addThrottlingReason(ThrottlingReason::OutsideViewport);
2570 else
2571 scriptedAnimationController->removeThrottlingReason(ThrottlingReason::OutsideViewport);

2796TiledBacking::Scrollability FrameView::computeScrollability() const
2797{
2798 auto* page = frame().page();
2799
2800 // Use smaller square tiles if the Window is not active to facilitate app napping.
2801 if (!page || !page->isWindowActive())
2802 return TiledBacking::HorizontallyScrollable | TiledBacking::VerticallyScrollable;
2803
2804 bool horizontallyScrollable;
2805 bool verticallyScrollable;
2806 bool clippedByAncestorView = static_cast<bool>(m_viewExposedRect);
2807
2808#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2809 if (page)
2810 clippedByAncestorView |= page->enclosedInScrollableAncestorView();
2811#endif
2812
2813 if (delegatesScrolling()) {
2814 IntSize documentSize = contentsSize();
2815 IntSize visibleSize = this->visibleSize();
2816
2817 horizontallyScrollable = clippedByAncestorView || documentSize.width() > visibleSize.width();
2818 verticallyScrollable = clippedByAncestorView || documentSize.height() > visibleSize.height();
2819 } else {
2820 horizontallyScrollable = clippedByAncestorView || horizontalScrollbar();
2821 verticallyScrollable = clippedByAncestorView || verticalScrollbar();
2822 }
2823
2824 TiledBacking::Scrollability scrollability = TiledBacking::NotScrollable;
2825 if (horizontallyScrollable)
2826 scrollability = TiledBacking::HorizontallyScrollable;
2827
2828 if (verticallyScrollable)
2829 scrollability |= TiledBacking::VerticallyScrollable;
2830
2831 return scrollability;
2832}

3062
3063FrameView::ExtendedBackgroundMode FrameView::calculateExtendedBackgroundMode() const
3064{
3065#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3066 // <rdar://problem/16201373>
3067 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3068#else
3069 if (!frame().settings().backgroundShouldExtendBeyondPage())
3070 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3071
3072 // Just because Settings::backgroundShouldExtendBeyondPage() is true does not necessarily mean
3073 // that the background rect needs to be extended for painting. Simple backgrounds can be extended
3074 // just with RenderLayerCompositor's rootExtendedBackgroundColor. More complicated backgrounds,
3075 // such as images, require extending the background rect to continue painting into the extended
3076 // region. This function finds out if it is necessary to extend the background rect for painting.
3077
3078 if (!frame().isMainFrame())
3079 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3080
3081 Document* document = frame().document();
3082 if (!document)
3083 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3084
3085 if (!renderView())
3086 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3087
3088 auto* rootBackgroundRenderer = renderView()->rendererForRootBackground();
3089 if (!rootBackgroundRenderer)
3090 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3091
3092 if (!rootBackgroundRenderer->style().hasBackgroundImage())
3093 return ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3094
3095 ExtendedBackgroundMode mode = ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3096 if (rootBackgroundRenderer->style().backgroundRepeatX() == FillRepeat::Repeat)
3097 mode |= ExtendedBackgroundModeHorizontal;
3098 if (rootBackgroundRenderer->style().backgroundRepeatY() == FillRepeat::Repeat)
3099 mode |= ExtendedBackgroundModeVertical;
3100
3101 return mode;
3102#endif
3103}
3104
3105void FrameView::updateTilesForExtendedBackgroundMode(ExtendedBackgroundMode mode)
3106{
3107 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
3108 if (!renderView)
3109 return;
3110
3111 RenderLayerBacking* backing = renderView->layer()->backing();
3112 if (!backing)
3113 return;
3114
3115 TiledBacking* tiledBacking = backing->tiledBacking();
3116 if (!tiledBacking)
3117 return;
3118
3119 ExtendedBackgroundMode existingMode = ExtendedBackgroundModeNone;
3120 if (tiledBacking->hasVerticalMargins())
3121 existingMode |= ExtendedBackgroundModeVertical;
3122 if (tiledBacking->hasHorizontalMargins())
3123 existingMode |= ExtendedBackgroundModeHorizontal;
3124
3125 if (existingMode == mode)
3126 return;
3127
3128 backing->setTiledBackingHasMargins(mode & ExtendedBackgroundModeHorizontal, mode & ExtendedBackgroundModeVertical);
3129}

3131IntRect FrameView::extendedBackgroundRectForPainting() const

3184void FrameView::scrollToAnchor()
3185{
3186 RefPtr<ContainerNode> anchorNode = m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor;
3187 if (!anchorNode)
3188 return;
3189
3190 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << *this << " scrollToAnchor() " << anchorNode.get());
3191
3192 if (!anchorNode->renderer())
3193 return;
3194
3195 m_shouldScrollToFocusedElement = false;
3196 m_delayedScrollToFocusedElementTimer.stop();
3197
3198 LayoutRect rect;
3199 bool insideFixed = false;
3200 if (anchorNode != frame().document() && anchorNode->renderer())
3201 rect = anchorNode->renderer()->absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(&insideFixed);
3202
3203 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << " anchor node rect " << rect);
3204
3205 // Scroll nested layers and frames to reveal the anchor.
3206 // Align to the top and to the closest side (this matches other browsers).
3207 if (anchorNode->renderer()->style().isHorizontalWritingMode())
3208 anchorNode->renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(rect, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ScrollAlignment::alignTopAlways, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
3209 else if (anchorNode->renderer()->style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
3210 anchorNode->renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(rect, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignRightAlways, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
3211 else
3212 anchorNode->renderer()->scrollRectToVisible(rect, insideFixed, { SelectionRevealMode::Reveal, ScrollAlignment::alignLeftAlways, ScrollAlignment::alignToEdgeIfNeeded, ShouldAllowCrossOriginScrolling::No });
3213
3214 if (AXObjectCache* cache = frame().document()->existingAXObjectCache())
3215 cache->handleScrolledToAnchor(anchorNode.get());
3216
3217 // scrollRectToVisible can call into setScrollPosition(), which resets m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor.
3218 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << " restoring anchor node to " << anchorNode.get());
3219 m_maintainScrollPositionAnchor = anchorNode;
3220 m_shouldScrollToFocusedElement = false;
3221 m_delayedScrollToFocusedElementTimer.stop();
3222}

3224void FrameView::updateEmbeddedObject(RenderEmbeddedObject& embeddedObject)
3225{
3226 // No need to update if it's already crashed or known to be missing.
3227 if (embeddedObject.isPluginUnavailable())
3228 return;
3229
3230 auto& element = embeddedObject.frameOwnerElement();
3231
3232 auto weakRenderer = makeWeakPtr(embeddedObject);
3233
3234 if (is<HTMLPlugInImageElement>(element)) {
3235 auto& pluginElement = downcast<HTMLPlugInImageElement>(element);
3236 if (pluginElement.needsWidgetUpdate())

3246 UNUSED_PARAM(ignoreWidgetState);

3250{

3370void FrameView::scheduleResizeEventIfNeeded()
3371{
3372 if (layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout() || needsLayout())
3373 return;
3374
3375 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
3376 if (!renderView || renderView->printing())
3377 return;
3378
3379 auto* page = frame().page();
3380 if (page && page->chrome().client().isSVGImageChromeClient())
3381 return;
3382
3383 IntSize currentSize = sizeForResizeEvent();
3384 float currentZoomFactor = renderView->style().zoom();
3385
3386 if (currentSize == m_lastViewportSize && currentZoomFactor == m_lastZoomFactor)
3387 return;
3388
3389 m_lastViewportSize = currentSize;
3390 m_lastZoomFactor = currentZoomFactor;
3391
3392 if (!layoutContext().didFirstLayout())
3393 return;
3394
3395#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3396 // Don't send the resize event if the document is loading. Some pages automatically reload
3397 // when the window is resized; Safari on iOS often resizes the window while setting up its
3398 // viewport. This obviously can cause problems.
3399 if (DocumentLoader* documentLoader = frame().loader().documentLoader()) {
3400 if (documentLoader->isLoadingInAPISense())
3401 return;
3402 }
3403#endif
3404
3405 auto* document = frame().document();
3406 if (document->quirks().shouldSilenceWindowResizeEvents()) {
3407 FRAMEVIEW_RELEASE_LOG(Events, "scheduleResizeEventIfNeeded: Not firing resize events because they are temporarily disabled for this page");
3408 return;
3409 }
3410
3411 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Events, stream << "FrameView " << this << " scheduleResizeEventIfNeeded scheduling resize event for document" << document << ", size " << currentSize);
3412 document->setNeedsDOMWindowResizeEvent();
3413
3414 bool isMainFrame = frame().isMainFrame();
3415 if (InspectorInstrumentation::hasFrontends() && isMainFrame) {
3416 if (InspectorClient* inspectorClient = page ? page->inspectorController().inspectorClient() : nullptr)
3417 inspectorClient->didResizeMainFrame(&frame());
3418 }

3433void FrameView::autoSizeIfEnabled()
3434{
3435 if (!m_shouldAutoSize)
3436 return;
3437
3438 if (m_inAutoSize)
3439 return;
3440
3441 auto* document = frame().document();
3442 if (!document)
3443 return;
3444
3445 auto* renderView = document->renderView();
3446 if (!renderView)
3447 return;
3448
3449 auto* firstChild = renderView->firstChild();
3450 if (!firstChild)
3451 return;
3452
3453 SetForScope<bool> changeInAutoSize(m_inAutoSize, true);
3454 if (layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot())
3455 layoutContext().convertSubtreeLayoutToFullLayout();
3456
3457 switch (m_autoSizeMode) {
3458 case AutoSizeMode::SizeToContent:
3459 performSizeToContentAutoSize();
3460 break;
3461 case AutoSizeMode::FixedWidth:
3462 performFixedWidthAutoSize();
3463 break;
3464 }
3465
3466 if (auto* page = frame().page(); page && frame().isMainFrame())
3467 page->chrome().client().intrinsicContentsSizeChanged(m_autoSizeContentSize);
3468
3469 m_didRunAutosize = true;
3470}
3471
3472void FrameView::performFixedWidthAutoSize()
3473{
3474 LOG(Layout, "FrameView %p performFixedWidthAutoSize", this);
3475
3476 auto* document = frame().document();
3477 auto* renderView = document->renderView();
3478 auto* firstChild = renderView->firstChild();
3479
3480 ScrollbarMode horizonalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
3481 ScrollbarMode verticalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
3482 setVerticalScrollbarLock(false);
3483 setHorizontalScrollbarLock(false);
3484 setScrollbarModes(horizonalScrollbarMode, verticalScrollbarMode, true, true);
3485
3486 ASSERT(is<RenderElement>(*firstChild));
3487 auto& documentRenderer = downcast<RenderElement>(*firstChild);
3488 documentRenderer.mutableStyle().setMaxWidth(Length(m_autoSizeConstraint.width(), LengthType::Fixed));
3489 resize(m_autoSizeConstraint.width(), m_autoSizeConstraint.height());
3490
3491 Ref<FrameView> protectedThis(*this);
3492 document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
3493 document->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
3494 // While the final content size could slightly be different after the next resize/layout (see below), we intentionally save and report
3495 // the current value to avoid unstable layout (e.g. content "height: 100%").
3496 // See also webkit.org/b/173561
3497 m_autoSizeContentSize = contentsSize();
3498
3499 auto finalWidth = std::max(m_autoSizeConstraint.width(), m_autoSizeContentSize.width());
3500 auto finalHeight = m_autoSizeFixedMinimumHeight ? std::max(m_autoSizeFixedMinimumHeight, m_autoSizeContentSize.height()) : m_autoSizeContentSize.height();
3501 resize(finalWidth, finalHeight);
3502 document->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
3503}
3504
3505void FrameView::performSizeToContentAutoSize()
3506{
3507 // Do the resizing twice. The first time is basically a rough calculation using the preferred width
3508 // which may result in a height change during the second iteration.
3509 // Let's ignore renderers with viewport units first and resolve these boxes during the second phase of the autosizing.
3510 LOG(Layout, "FrameView %p performSizeToContentAutoSize", this);
3511 ASSERT(frame().document() && frame().document()->renderView());
3512
3513 auto& document = *frame().document();
3514 auto& renderView = *document.renderView();
3515 auto layoutWithAdjustedStyleIfNeeded = [&] {
3516 document.updateStyleIfNeeded();
3517 if (auto* documentRenderer = downcast<RenderElement>(renderView.firstChild())) {
3518 auto& style = documentRenderer->mutableStyle();
3519 if (style.logicalHeight().isPercent()) {
3520 // Percent height values on the document renderer when we don't really have a proper viewport size can
3521 // result incorrect rendering in certain layout contexts (e.g flex).
3522 style.setLogicalHeight({ });
3523 }
3524 }
3525 document.updateLayout();
3526 };
3527
3528 resetOverriddenViewportWidthForCSSViewportUnits();
3529 // Start from the minimum size and allow it to grow.
3530 auto minAutoSize = IntSize { 1, 1 };
3531 resize(minAutoSize);
3532 auto size = frameRect().size();
3533 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
3534 layoutWithAdjustedStyleIfNeeded();
3535 // Update various sizes including contentsSize, scrollHeight, etc.
3536 auto newSize = IntSize { renderView.minPreferredLogicalWidth(), renderView.documentRect().height() };
3537
3538 // Check to see if a scrollbar is needed for a given dimension and
3539 // if so, increase the other dimension to account for the scrollbar.
3540 // Since the dimensions are only for the view rectangle, once a
3541 // dimension exceeds the maximum, there is no need to increase it further.
3542 if (newSize.width() > m_autoSizeConstraint.width()) {
3543 RefPtr<Scrollbar> localHorizontalScrollbar = horizontalScrollbar();
3544 if (!localHorizontalScrollbar)
3545 localHorizontalScrollbar = createScrollbar(HorizontalScrollbar);
3546 newSize.expand(0, localHorizontalScrollbar->occupiedHeight());
3547 // Don't bother checking for a vertical scrollbar because the width is at
3548 // already greater the maximum.
3549 } else if (newSize.height() > m_autoSizeConstraint.height()) {
3550 RefPtr<Scrollbar> localVerticalScrollbar = verticalScrollbar();
3551 if (!localVerticalScrollbar)
3552 localVerticalScrollbar = createScrollbar(VerticalScrollbar);
3553 newSize.expand(localVerticalScrollbar->occupiedWidth(), 0);
3554 // Don't bother checking for a horizontal scrollbar because the height is
3555 // already greater the maximum.
3556 }
3557
3558 // Ensure the size is at least the min bounds.
3559 newSize = newSize.expandedTo(minAutoSize);
3560
3561 // Bound the dimensions by the max bounds and determine what scrollbars to show.
3562 ScrollbarMode horizonalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
3563 if (newSize.width() > m_autoSizeConstraint.width()) {
3564 newSize.setWidth(m_autoSizeConstraint.width());
3565 horizonalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOn;
3566 }
3567 ScrollbarMode verticalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOff;
3568 if (newSize.height() > m_autoSizeConstraint.height()) {
3569 newSize.setHeight(m_autoSizeConstraint.height());
3570 verticalScrollbarMode = ScrollbarAlwaysOn;
3571 }
3572
3573 if (newSize == size)
3574 continue;
3575
3576 // While loading only allow the size to increase (to avoid twitching during intermediate smaller states)
3577 // unless autoresize has just been turned on or the maximum size is smaller than the current size.
3578 if (m_didRunAutosize && size.height() <= m_autoSizeConstraint.height() && size.width() <= m_autoSizeConstraint.width()
3579 && !frame().loader().isComplete() && (newSize.height() < size.height() || newSize.width() < size.width()))
3580 break;
3581
3582 // The first time around, resize to the minimum height again; otherwise,
3583 // on pages (e.g. quirks mode) where the body/document resize to the view size,
3584 // we'll end up not shrinking back down after resizing to the computed preferred width.
3585 resize(newSize.width(), i ? newSize.height() : minAutoSize.height());
3586 // Protect the content from evergrowing layout.
3587 auto preferredViewportWidth = std::min(newSize.width(), m_autoSizeConstraint.width());
3588 overrideViewportWidthForCSSViewportUnits(preferredViewportWidth);
3589 // Force the scrollbar state to avoid the scrollbar code adding them and causing them to be needed. For example,
3590 // a vertical scrollbar may cause text to wrap and thus increase the height (which is the only reason the scollbar is needed).
3591 setVerticalScrollbarLock(false);
3592 setHorizontalScrollbarLock(false);
3593 setScrollbarModes(horizonalScrollbarMode, verticalScrollbarMode, true, true);
3594 }
3595 // All the resizing above may have invalidated style (for example if viewport units are being used).
3596 // FIXME: Use the final layout's result as the content size (webkit.org/b/173561).
3597 layoutWithAdjustedStyleIfNeeded();
3598 m_autoSizeContentSize = contentsSize();
3599}

3689IntRect FrameView::windowClipRect() const
3690{
3691 ASSERT(frame().view() == this);
3692
3693 if (m_cachedWindowClipRect)
3694 return *m_cachedWindowClipRect;
3695
3696 if (paintsEntireContents())
3697 return contentsToWindow(IntRect(IntPoint(), totalContentsSize()));
3698
3699 // Set our clip rect to be our contents.
3700 IntRect clipRect = contentsToWindow(visibleContentRect(LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect));
3701
3702 if (!frame().ownerElement())
3703 return clipRect;
3704
3705 // Take our owner element and get its clip rect.
3706 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* ownerElement = frame().ownerElement();
3707 if (FrameView* parentView = ownerElement->document().view())
3708 clipRect.intersect(parentView->windowClipRectForFrameOwner(ownerElement, true));
3709 return clipRect;
3710}
3711
3712IntRect FrameView::windowClipRectForFrameOwner(const HTMLFrameOwnerElement* ownerElement, bool clipToLayerContents) const
3713{
3714 // The renderer can sometimes be null when style="display:none" interacts
3715 // with external content and plugins.
3716 if (!ownerElement->renderer())
3717 return windowClipRect();
3718
3719 // If we have no layer, just return our window clip rect.
3720 const RenderLayer* enclosingLayer = ownerElement->renderer()->enclosingLayer();
3721 if (!enclosingLayer)
3722 return windowClipRect();
3723
3724 // Apply the clip from the layer.
3725 IntRect clipRect;
3726 if (clipToLayerContents)
3727 clipRect = snappedIntRect(enclosingLayer->childrenClipRect());
3728 else
3729 clipRect = snappedIntRect(enclosingLayer->selfClipRect());
3730 clipRect = contentsToWindow(clipRect);
3731 return intersection(clipRect, windowClipRect());
3732}
