3769float FrameView::adjustScrollStepForFixedContent(float step, ScrollbarOrientation orientation, ScrollGranularity granularity)
3770{
3771 if (granularity != ScrollByPage || orientation == HorizontalScrollbar)
3772 return step;
3773
3774 TrackedRendererListHashSet* positionedObjects = nullptr;
3775 if (RenderView* root = frame().contentRenderer()) {
3776 if (!root->hasPositionedObjects())
3777 return step;
3778 positionedObjects = root->positionedObjects();
3779 }
3780
3781 FloatRect unobscuredContentRect = this->unobscuredContentRect();
3782 float topObscuredArea = 0;
3783 float bottomObscuredArea = 0;
3784 for (const auto& positionedObject : *positionedObjects) {
3785 const RenderStyle& style = positionedObject->style();
3786 if (style.position() != PositionType::Fixed || style.visibility() == Visibility::Hidden || !style.opacity())
3787 continue;
3788
3789 FloatQuad contentQuad = positionedObject->absoluteContentQuad();
3790 if (!contentQuad.isRectilinear())
3791 continue;
3792
3793 FloatRect contentBoundingBox = contentQuad.boundingBox();
3794 FloatRect fixedRectInView = intersection(unobscuredContentRect, contentBoundingBox);
3795
3796 if (fixedRectInView.width() < unobscuredContentRect.width())
3797 continue;
3798
3799 if (fixedRectInView.y() == unobscuredContentRect.y())
3800 topObscuredArea = std::max(topObscuredArea, fixedRectInView.height());
3801 else if (fixedRectInView.maxY() == unobscuredContentRect.maxY())
3802 bottomObscuredArea = std::max(bottomObscuredArea, fixedRectInView.height());
3803 }
3804
3805 return Scrollbar::pageStep(unobscuredContentRect.height(), unobscuredContentRect.height() - topObscuredArea - bottomObscuredArea);
3806}

3872bool FrameView::isScrollable(Scrollability definitionOfScrollable)
3873{
3874 // Check for:
3875 // 1) If there an actual overflow.
3876 // 2) display:none or visibility:hidden set to self or inherited.
3877 // 3) overflow{-x,-y}: hidden;
3878 // 4) scrolling: no;
3879 if (!didFirstLayout())
3880 return false;
3881
3882 bool requiresActualOverflowToBeConsideredScrollable = !frame().isMainFrame() || definitionOfScrollable != Scrollability::ScrollableOrRubberbandable;
3883#if !ENABLE(RUBBER_BANDING)
3884 requiresActualOverflowToBeConsideredScrollable = true;
3885#endif
3886
3887 // Covers #1
3888 if (requiresActualOverflowToBeConsideredScrollable) {
3889 IntSize totalContentsSize = this->totalContentsSize();
3890 IntSize visibleContentSize = visibleContentRect(LegacyIOSDocumentVisibleRect).size();
3891 if (totalContentsSize.height() <= visibleContentSize.height() && totalContentsSize.width() <= visibleContentSize.width())
3892 return false;
3893 }
3894
3895 // Covers #2.
3896 HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = frame().ownerElement();
3897 if (owner && (!owner->renderer() || !owner->renderer()->visibleToHitTesting()))
3898 return false;
3899
3900 // Cover #3 and #4.
3901 ScrollbarMode horizontalMode;
3902 ScrollbarMode verticalMode;
3903 calculateScrollbarModesForLayout(horizontalMode, verticalMode, RulesFromWebContentOnly);
3904 if (horizontalMode == ScrollbarAlwaysOff && verticalMode == ScrollbarAlwaysOff)
3905 return false;
3906
3907 return true;
3908}

3913}

3915bool FrameView::hasScrollableOrRubberbandableAncestor()

3921 Scrollability frameScrollability = parent->frame().isMainFrame() ? Scrollability::ScrollableOrRubberbandable : Scrollability::Scrollable;
3922 if (parent->isScrollable(frameScrollability))

3985void FrameView::updateScrollCorner()
3986{
3987 RenderElement* renderer = nullptr;
3988 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> cornerStyle;
3989 IntRect cornerRect = scrollCornerRect();
3990
3991 if (!cornerRect.isEmpty()) {
3992 // Try the <body> element first as a scroll corner source.
3993 Document* doc = frame().document();
3994 Element* body = doc ? doc->bodyOrFrameset() : nullptr;
3995 if (body && body->renderer()) {
3996 renderer = body->renderer();
3997 cornerStyle = renderer->getUncachedPseudoStyle({ PseudoId::ScrollbarCorner }, &renderer->style());
3998 }
3999
4000 if (!cornerStyle) {
4001 // If the <body> didn't have a custom style, then the root element might.
4002 Element* docElement = doc ? doc->documentElement() : nullptr;
4003 if (docElement && docElement->renderer()) {
4004 renderer = docElement->renderer();
4005 cornerStyle = renderer->getUncachedPseudoStyle({ PseudoId::ScrollbarCorner }, &renderer->style());
4006 }
4007 }
4008
4009 if (!cornerStyle) {
4010 // If we have an owning iframe/frame element, then it can set the custom scrollbar also.
4011 // FIXME: Seems wrong to do this for cross-origin frames.
4012 if (RenderWidget* renderer = frame().ownerRenderer())
4013 cornerStyle = renderer->getUncachedPseudoStyle({ PseudoId::ScrollbarCorner }, &renderer->style());
4014 }
4015 }
4016
4017 if (!cornerStyle)
4018 m_scrollCorner = nullptr;
4019 else {
4020 if (!m_scrollCorner) {
4021 m_scrollCorner = createRenderer<RenderScrollbarPart>(renderer->document(), WTFMove(*cornerStyle));
4022 m_scrollCorner->initializeStyle();
4023 } else
4024 m_scrollCorner->setStyle(WTFMove(*cornerStyle));
4025 invalidateScrollCorner(cornerRect);
4026 }
4027}

4030{
4031 if (context.invalidatingControlTints()) {
4032 updateScrollCorner();
4033 return;
4034 }
4035
4036 if (m_scrollCorner) {
4037 if (frame().isMainFrame())
4038 context.fillRect(cornerRect, baseBackgroundColor());
4039 m_scrollCorner->paintIntoRect(context, cornerRect.location(), cornerRect);
4040 return;
4041 }
4042
4043#if PLATFORM(MAC)
4044 // Keep this in sync with ScrollAnimatorMac's effectiveAppearanceForScrollerImp:.
4045 LocalDefaultSystemAppearance localAppearance(useDarkAppearanceForScrollbars());
4046#endif
4047
4048 ScrollView::paintScrollCorner(context, cornerRect);
4049}

4061
4062Color FrameView::documentBackgroundColor() const
4063{
4064 // <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=59540> We blend the background color of
4065 // the document and the body against the base background color of the frame view.
4066 // Background images are unfortunately impractical to include.
4067
4068 // Return invalid Color objects whenever there is insufficient information.
4069 if (!frame().document())
4070 return Color();
4071
4072 auto* htmlElement = frame().document()->documentElement();
4073 auto* bodyElement = frame().document()->bodyOrFrameset();
4074
4075 // Start with invalid colors.
4076 Color htmlBackgroundColor;
4077 Color bodyBackgroundColor;
4078 if (htmlElement && htmlElement->renderer())
4079 htmlBackgroundColor = htmlElement->renderer()->style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
4080 if (bodyElement && bodyElement->renderer())
4081 bodyBackgroundColor = bodyElement->renderer()->style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
4082
4083 if (!bodyBackgroundColor.isValid()) {
4084 if (!htmlBackgroundColor.isValid())
4085 return Color();
4086 return blendSourceOver(baseBackgroundColor(), htmlBackgroundColor);
4087 }
4088
4089 if (!htmlBackgroundColor.isValid())
4090 return blendSourceOver(baseBackgroundColor(), bodyBackgroundColor);
4091
4092 // We take the aggregate of the base background color
4093 // the <html> background color, and the <body>
4094 // background color to find the document color. The
4095 // addition of the base background color is not
4096 // technically part of the document background, but it
4097 // otherwise poses problems when the aggregate is not
4098 // fully opaque.
4099 return blendSourceOver(blendSourceOver(baseBackgroundColor(), htmlBackgroundColor), bodyBackgroundColor);
4100}

4151
4152void FrameView::updateControlTints()
4153{
4154 // This is called when control tints are changed from aqua/graphite to clear and vice versa.
4155 // We do a "fake" paint, and when the theme gets a paint call, it can then do an invalidate.
4156 // This is only done if the theme supports control tinting. It's up to the theme and platform
4157 // to define when controls get the tint and to call this function when that changes.
4158
4159 // Optimize the common case where we bring a window to the front while it's still empty.
4160 if (frame().document()->url().isEmpty())
4161 return;
4162
4163 // As noted above, this is a "fake" paint, so we should pause counting relevant repainted objects.
4164 Page* page = frame().page();
4165 bool isCurrentlyCountingRelevantRepaintedObject = false;
4166 if (page) {
4167 isCurrentlyCountingRelevantRepaintedObject = page->isCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects();
4168 page->setIsCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects(false);
4169 }
4170
4171 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
4172 if ((renderView && renderView->theme().supportsControlTints()) || hasCustomScrollbars())
4173 invalidateControlTints();
4174
4175 if (page)
4176 page->setIsCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects(isCurrentlyCountingRelevantRepaintedObject);
4177}

4212void FrameView::willPaintContents(GraphicsContext& context, const IntRect&, PaintingState& paintingState)
4213{
4214 Document* document = frame().document();
4215
4216 if (!context.paintingDisabled())
4217 InspectorInstrumentation::willPaint(*renderView());
4218
4219 paintingState.isTopLevelPainter = !sCurrentPaintTimeStamp;
4220
4221 if (paintingState.isTopLevelPainter)
4222 sCurrentPaintTimeStamp = MonotonicTime::now();
4223
4224 paintingState.paintBehavior = m_paintBehavior;
4225
4226 if (FrameView* parentView = parentFrameView()) {
4227 if (parentView->paintBehavior() & PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers)
4228 m_paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers);
4229
4230 if (parentView->paintBehavior() & PaintBehavior::Snapshotting)
4231 m_paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
4232
4233 if (parentView->paintBehavior() & PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint)
4234 m_paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::TileFirstPaint);
4235 }
4236
4237 if (document->printing()) {
4238 m_paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers);
4239 m_paintBehavior.add(PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
4240 }
4241
4242 paintingState.isFlatteningPaintOfRootFrame = (m_paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers) && !frame().ownerElement() && !context.detectingContentfulPaint();
4243 if (paintingState.isFlatteningPaintOfRootFrame)
4244 notifyWidgetsInAllFrames(WillPaintFlattened);
4245
4246 ASSERT(!m_isPainting);
4247 m_isPainting = true;
4248}

4250void FrameView::didPaintContents(GraphicsContext& context, const IntRect& dirtyRect, PaintingState& paintingState)
4251{
4252 m_isPainting = false;
4253
4254 if (paintingState.isFlatteningPaintOfRootFrame)
4255 notifyWidgetsInAllFrames(DidPaintFlattened);
4256
4257 m_paintBehavior = paintingState.paintBehavior;
4258 m_lastPaintTime = MonotonicTime::now();
4259
4260 if (paintingState.isTopLevelPainter)
4261 sCurrentPaintTimeStamp = MonotonicTime();
4262
4263 if (!context.paintingDisabled()) {
4264 InspectorInstrumentation::didPaint(*renderView(), dirtyRect);

4266 firePaintRelatedMilestonesIfNeeded();

4270void FrameView::paintContents(GraphicsContext& context, const IntRect& dirtyRect, SecurityOriginPaintPolicy securityOriginPaintPolicy, EventRegionContext* eventRegionContext)
4271{
4272#ifndef NDEBUG
4273 bool fillWithWarningColor;
4274 if (frame().document()->printing())
4275 fillWithWarningColor = false; // Printing, don't fill with red (can't remember why).
4276 else if (frame().ownerElement())
4277 fillWithWarningColor = false; // Subframe, don't fill with red.
4278 else if (isTransparent())
4279 fillWithWarningColor = false; // Transparent, don't fill with red.
4280 else if (m_paintBehavior & PaintBehavior::SelectionOnly)
4281 fillWithWarningColor = false; // Selections are transparent, don't fill with red.
4282 else if (m_nodeToDraw)
4283 fillWithWarningColor = false; // Element images are transparent, don't fill with red.
4284 else
4285 fillWithWarningColor = true;
4286
4287 if (fillWithWarningColor) {
4288 IntRect debugRect = frameRect();
4289 debugRect.intersect(dirtyRect);
4290 context.fillRect(debugRect, SRGBA<uint8_t> { 255, 64, 255 });
4291 }
4292#endif
4293
4294 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
4295 if (!renderView) {
4296 LOG_ERROR("called FrameView::paint with nil renderer");
4297 return;
4298 }
4299
4300 if (!layoutContext().inPaintableState())
4301 return;
4302
4303 ASSERT(!needsLayout());
4304 if (needsLayout()) {
4305 FRAMEVIEW_RELEASE_LOG(Layout, "paintContents: Not painting because render tree needs layout");
4306 return;
4307 }
4308
4309 PaintingState paintingState;
4310 willPaintContents(context, dirtyRect, paintingState);
4311
4312 // m_nodeToDraw is used to draw only one element (and its descendants)
4313 RenderObject* renderer = m_nodeToDraw ? m_nodeToDraw->renderer() : nullptr;
4314 RenderLayer* rootLayer = renderView->layer();
4315
4316 RenderObject::SetLayoutNeededForbiddenScope forbidSetNeedsLayout(rootLayer->renderer());
4317
4318 // To work around http://webkit.org/b/135106, ensure that the paint root isn't an inline with culled line boxes.
4319 // FIXME: This can cause additional content to be included in the snapshot, so remove this once that bug is fixed.
4320 while (is<RenderInline>(renderer) && !downcast<RenderInline>(*renderer).firstLineBox())
4321 renderer = renderer->parent();
4322
4323 rootLayer->paint(context, dirtyRect, LayoutSize(), m_paintBehavior, renderer, { }, securityOriginPaintPolicy == SecurityOriginPaintPolicy::AnyOrigin ? RenderLayer::SecurityOriginPaintPolicy::AnyOrigin : RenderLayer::SecurityOriginPaintPolicy::AccessibleOriginOnly, eventRegionContext);
4324 if (auto* scrollableRootLayer = rootLayer->scrollableArea()) {
4325 if (scrollableRootLayer->containsDirtyOverlayScrollbars() && !eventRegionContext)
4326 scrollableRootLayer->paintOverlayScrollbars(context, dirtyRect, m_paintBehavior, renderer);
4327 }
4328
4329 didPaintContents(context, dirtyRect, paintingState);
4330}

4353void FrameView::paintContentsForSnapshot(GraphicsContext& context, const IntRect& imageRect, SelectionInSnapshot shouldPaintSelection, CoordinateSpaceForSnapshot coordinateSpace)
4354{
4355 updateLayoutAndStyleIfNeededRecursive();
4356
4357 // Cache paint behavior and set a new behavior appropriate for snapshots.
4358 auto oldBehavior = paintBehavior();
4359 setPaintBehavior(oldBehavior | PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers | PaintBehavior::Snapshotting);
4360
4361 // If the snapshot should exclude selection, then we'll clear the current selection
4362 // in the render tree only. This will allow us to restore the selection from the DOM
4363 // after we paint the snapshot.
4364 if (shouldPaintSelection == ExcludeSelection) {
4365 for (auto* frame = m_frame.ptr(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext(m_frame.ptr())) {
4366 if (auto* renderView = frame->contentRenderer())
4367 renderView->selection().clear();
4368 }
4369 }
4370
4371 if (coordinateSpace == DocumentCoordinates)
4372 paintContents(context, imageRect);
4373 else {
4374 // A snapshot in ViewCoordinates will include a scrollbar, and the snapshot will contain
4375 // whatever content the document is currently scrolled to.
4376 paint(context, imageRect);
4377 }
4378
4379 // Restore selection.
4380 if (shouldPaintSelection == ExcludeSelection) {
4381 for (auto* frame = m_frame.ptr(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext(m_frame.ptr()))
4382 frame->selection().updateAppearance();
4383 }
4384
4385 // Restore cached paint behavior.
4386 setPaintBehavior(oldBehavior);
4387}

4399
4400void FrameView::updateLayoutAndStyleIfNeededRecursive()
4401{
4402 // Style updating, render tree creation, and layout needs to be done multiple times
4403 // for more than one reason. But one reason is that when an <object> element determines
4404 // what it needs to load a subframe, a second pass is needed. That requires update
4405 // passes equal to the number of levels of DOM nesting. That is why this number is large.
4406 // There are test cases where we have roughly 10 levels of DOM nesting, so this needs to
4407 // be greater than that. We have a limit to avoid the possibility of an infinite loop.
4408 // Typical calls will run the loop 2 times (once to do work, once to detect no further work
4409 // is needed).
4410 // FIXME: We should find an approach that does not require a loop at all.
4411 const unsigned maxUpdatePasses = 25;
4412
4413 // Style updates can trigger script, which can cause this FrameView to be destroyed.
4414 Ref<FrameView> protectedThis(*this);
4415
4416 using DescendantsDeque = Deque<Ref<FrameView>, 16>;
4417 auto nextRenderedDescendant = [this] (DescendantsDeque& descendantsDeque) -> RefPtr<FrameView> {
4418 if (descendantsDeque.isEmpty())
4419 descendantsDeque.append(*this);
4420 else {
4421 // Append renderered children after processing the parent, in case the processing
4422 // affects the set of rendered children.
4423 auto previousView = descendantsDeque.takeFirst();
4424 for (auto* frame = previousView->frame().tree().firstRenderedChild(); frame; frame = frame->tree().nextRenderedSibling()) {
4425 if (auto* view = frame->view())
4426 descendantsDeque.append(*view);
4427 }
4428 if (descendantsDeque.isEmpty())
4429 return nullptr;
4430 }
4431 return descendantsDeque.first().ptr();
4432 };
4433
4434 for (unsigned i = 0; i < maxUpdatePasses; ++i) {
4435 bool didWork = false;
4436 DescendantsDeque deque;
4437 while (auto view = nextRenderedDescendant(deque)) {
4438 if (view->frame().document()->updateStyleIfNeeded())
4439 didWork = true;
4440 if (view->needsLayout()) {
4441 view->layoutContext().layout();
4442 didWork = true;
4443 }
4444 }
4445 if (!didWork)
4446 break;
4447 }
4448
4449#if ASSERT_ENABLED
4450 auto needsStyleRecalc = [&] {
4451 DescendantsDeque deque;
4452 while (auto view = nextRenderedDescendant(deque)) {
4453 auto* document = view->frame().document();
4454 if (document && document->childNeedsStyleRecalc())
4455 return true;
4456 }
4457 return false;
4458 };
4459
4460 auto needsLayout = [&] {
4461 DescendantsDeque deque;
4462 while (auto view = nextRenderedDescendant(deque)) {
4463 if (view->needsLayout())
4464 return true;
4465 }
4466 return false;
4467 };
4468#endif // ASSERT_ENABLED
4469
4470 ASSERT(!needsStyleRecalc());
4471 ASSERT(!needsLayout());
4472}

4474void FrameView::incrementVisuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount(const String& inlineText)
4475{
4476 if (m_visuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount > visualCharacterThreshold && m_hasReachedSignificantRenderedTextThreshold)
4477 return;
4478
4479 auto nonWhitespaceLength = [](auto& inlineText) {
4480 auto length = inlineText.length();
4481 for (unsigned i = 0; i < inlineText.length(); ++i) {
4482 if (isNotHTMLSpace(inlineText[i]))
4483 continue;
4484 --length;
4485 }
4486 return length;
4487 };
4488 m_visuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount += nonWhitespaceLength(inlineText);
4489 ++m_textRendererCountForVisuallyNonEmptyCharacters;
4490}
4491
4492void FrameView::updateHasReachedSignificantRenderedTextThreshold()
4493{
4494 if (m_hasReachedSignificantRenderedTextThreshold)
4495 return;
4496
4497 auto* page = frame().page();
4498 if (!page || !page->requestedLayoutMilestones().contains(DidRenderSignificantAmountOfText))
4499 return;
4500
4501 auto* document = frame().document();
4502 if (!document)
4503 return;
4504
4505 document->updateMainArticleElementAfterLayout();
4506 auto hasMainArticleElement = document->hasMainArticleElement();
4507 auto characterThreshold = hasMainArticleElement ? mainArticleSignificantRenderedTextCharacterThreshold : defaultSignificantRenderedTextCharacterThreshold;
4508 if (m_visuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount < characterThreshold)
4509 return;
4510
4511 auto meanLength = hasMainArticleElement ? mainArticleSignificantRenderedTextMeanLength : defaultSignificantRenderedTextMeanLength;
4512 if (!m_textRendererCountForVisuallyNonEmptyCharacters || m_visuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount / static_cast<float>(m_textRendererCountForVisuallyNonEmptyCharacters) < meanLength)
4513 return;
4514
4515 m_hasReachedSignificantRenderedTextThreshold = true;
4516}

4526
4527void FrameView::checkAndDispatchDidReachVisuallyNonEmptyState()
4528{
4529 auto qualifiesAsVisuallyNonEmpty = [&] {
4530 // No content yet.
4531 auto& document = *frame().document();
4532 auto* documentElement = document.documentElement();
4533 if (!documentElement || !documentElement->renderer())
4534 return false;
4535
4536 if (document.hasVisuallyNonEmptyCustomContent())
4537 return true;
4538
4539 // FIXME: We should also ignore renderers with non-final style.
4540 if (document.styleScope().hasPendingSheetsBeforeBody())
4541 return false;
4542
4543 auto finishedParsingMainDocument = frame().loader().stateMachine().committedFirstRealDocumentLoad() && (document.readyState() == Document::Interactive || document.readyState() == Document::Complete);
4544 // Ensure that we always fire visually non-empty milestone eventually.
4545 if (finishedParsingMainDocument && frame().loader().isComplete())
4546 return true;
4547
4548 auto isVisible = [](const Element* element) {
4549 if (!element || !element->renderer())
4550 return false;
4551 if (!element->renderer()->opacity())
4552 return false;
4553 return element->renderer()->style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible;
4554 };
4555
4556 if (!isVisible(documentElement))
4557 return false;
4558
4559 if (!isVisible(document.body()))
4560 return false;
4561
4562 // The first few hundred characters rarely contain the interesting content of the page.
4563 if (m_visuallyNonEmptyCharacterCount > visualCharacterThreshold)
4564 return true;
4565
4566 // Use a threshold value to prevent very small amounts of visible content from triggering didFirstVisuallyNonEmptyLayout
4567 if (m_visuallyNonEmptyPixelCount > visualPixelThreshold)
4568 return true;
4569
4570 auto isMoreContentExpected = [&]() {
4571 ASSERT(finishedParsingMainDocument);
4572 // Pending css/font loading means we should wait a little longer. Classic non-async, non-defer scripts are all processed by now.
4573 auto* documentLoader = frame().loader().documentLoader();
4574 if (!documentLoader)
4575 return false;
4576
4577 auto& resourceLoader = documentLoader->cachedResourceLoader();
4578 if (!resourceLoader.requestCount())
4579 return false;
4580
4581 auto& resources = resourceLoader.allCachedResources();
4582 for (auto& resource : resources) {
4583 if (resource.value->isLoaded())
4584 continue;
4585 if (resource.value->type() == CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet || resource.value->type() == CachedResource::Type::FontResource)
4586 return true;
4587 }
4588 return false;
4589 };
4590
4591 // Finished parsing the main document and we still don't yet have enough content. Check if we might be getting some more.
4592 if (finishedParsingMainDocument)
4593 return !isMoreContentExpected();
4594
4595 return false;
4596 };
4597
4598 if (m_contentQualifiesAsVisuallyNonEmpty)
4599 return;
4600
4601 if (!qualifiesAsVisuallyNonEmpty())
4602 return;
4603
4604 m_contentQualifiesAsVisuallyNonEmpty = true;
4605 if (frame().isMainFrame())
4606 frame().loader().didReachVisuallyNonEmptyState();
4607}

4667
4668void FrameView::forceLayoutForPagination(const FloatSize& pageSize, const FloatSize& originalPageSize, float maximumShrinkFactor, AdjustViewSizeOrNot shouldAdjustViewSize)
4669{
4670 if (!renderView())
4671 return;
4672
4673 Ref<FrameView> protectedThis(*this);
4674 auto& renderView = *this->renderView();
4675
4676 // Dumping externalRepresentation(frame().renderer()).ascii() is a good trick to see
4677 // the state of things before and after the layout
4678 float pageLogicalWidth = renderView.style().isHorizontalWritingMode() ? pageSize.width() : pageSize.height();
4679 float pageLogicalHeight = renderView.style().isHorizontalWritingMode() ? pageSize.height() : pageSize.width();
4680
4681 renderView.setPageLogicalSize({ floor(pageLogicalWidth), floor(pageLogicalHeight) });
4682 renderView.setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
4683 forceLayout();
4684 if (hasOneRef())
4685 return;
4686
4687 // If we don't fit in the given page width, we'll lay out again. If we don't fit in the
4688 // page width when shrunk, we will lay out at maximum shrink and clip extra content.
4689 // FIXME: We are assuming a shrink-to-fit printing implementation. A cropping
4690 // implementation should not do this!
4691 bool horizontalWritingMode = renderView.style().isHorizontalWritingMode();
4692 const LayoutRect& documentRect = renderView.documentRect();
4693 LayoutUnit docLogicalWidth = horizontalWritingMode ? documentRect.width() : documentRect.height();
4694 if (docLogicalWidth > pageLogicalWidth) {
4695 int expectedPageWidth = std::min<float>(documentRect.width(), pageSize.width() * maximumShrinkFactor);
4696 int expectedPageHeight = std::min<float>(documentRect.height(), pageSize.height() * maximumShrinkFactor);
4697 FloatSize maxPageSize = frame().resizePageRectsKeepingRatio(FloatSize(originalPageSize.width(), originalPageSize.height()), FloatSize(expectedPageWidth, expectedPageHeight));
4698 pageLogicalWidth = horizontalWritingMode ? maxPageSize.width() : maxPageSize.height();
4699 pageLogicalHeight = horizontalWritingMode ? maxPageSize.height() : maxPageSize.width();
4700
4701 renderView.setPageLogicalSize({ floor(pageLogicalWidth), floor(pageLogicalHeight) });
4702 renderView.setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
4703 forceLayout();
4704 if (hasOneRef())
4705 return;
4706
4707 const LayoutRect& updatedDocumentRect = renderView.documentRect();
4708 LayoutUnit docLogicalHeight = horizontalWritingMode ? updatedDocumentRect.height() : updatedDocumentRect.width();
4709 LayoutUnit docLogicalTop = horizontalWritingMode ? updatedDocumentRect.y() : updatedDocumentRect.x();
4710 LayoutUnit docLogicalRight = horizontalWritingMode ? updatedDocumentRect.maxX() : updatedDocumentRect.maxY();
4711 LayoutUnit clippedLogicalLeft;
4712 if (!renderView.style().isLeftToRightDirection())
4713 clippedLogicalLeft = docLogicalRight - pageLogicalWidth;
4714 LayoutRect overflow { clippedLogicalLeft, docLogicalTop, LayoutUnit(pageLogicalWidth), docLogicalHeight };
4715
4716 if (!horizontalWritingMode)
4717 overflow = overflow.transposedRect();
4718 renderView.clearLayoutOverflow();
4719 renderView.addLayoutOverflow(overflow); // This is how we clip in case we overflow again.
4720 }
4721
4722 if (shouldAdjustViewSize)
4723 adjustViewSize();
4724}
4725
4726void FrameView::adjustPageHeightDeprecated(float *newBottom, float oldTop, float oldBottom, float /*bottomLimit*/)
4727{
4728 RenderView* renderView = this->renderView();
4729 if (!renderView) {
4730 *newBottom = oldBottom;
4731 return;
4732
4733 }
4734 // Use a context with painting disabled.
4735 NullGraphicsContext context(NullGraphicsContext::PaintInvalidationReasons::None);
4736 renderView->setTruncatedAt(static_cast<int>(floorf(oldBottom)));
4737 IntRect dirtyRect(0, static_cast<int>(floorf(oldTop)), renderView->layoutOverflowRect().maxX(), static_cast<int>(ceilf(oldBottom - oldTop)));
4738 renderView->setPrintRect(dirtyRect);
4739 renderView->layer()->paint(context, dirtyRect);
4740 *newBottom = renderView->bestTruncatedAt();
4741 if (!*newBottom)
4742 *newBottom = oldBottom;
4743 renderView->setPrintRect(IntRect());
4744}

5028void FrameView::setTracksRepaints(bool trackRepaints)
5029{
5030 if (trackRepaints == m_isTrackingRepaints)
5031 return;
5032
5033 // Force layout to flush out any pending repaints.
5034 if (trackRepaints) {
5035 if (frame().document())
5036 frame().document()->updateLayout();
5037 }
5038
5039 for (Frame* frame = &m_frame->tree().top(); frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext()) {
5040 if (RenderView* renderView = frame->contentRenderer())
5041 renderView->compositor().setTracksRepaints(trackRepaints);
5042 }
5043
5044 resetTrackedRepaints();
5045 m_isTrackingRepaints = trackRepaints;
5046}

5049{
5050 m_trackedRepaintRects.clear();

5052 renderView->compositor().resetTrackedRepaintRects();
5053}

5061 document->updateLayout();
5062
5063 TextStream ts;
5064 if (!m_trackedRepaintRects.isEmpty()) {
5065 ts << "(repaint rects\n";
5066 for (auto& rect : m_trackedRepaintRects)
5067 ts << " (rect " << LayoutUnit(rect.x()) << " " << LayoutUnit(rect.y()) << " " << LayoutUnit(rect.width()) << " " << LayoutUnit(rect.height()) << ")\n";

5131bool FrameView::handleWheelEventForScrolling(const PlatformWheelEvent& wheelEvent, std::optional<WheelScrollGestureState> gestureState)
5132{
5133 // Note that to allow for rubber-band over-scroll behavior, even non-scrollable views
5134 // should handle wheel events.
5135#if !ENABLE(RUBBER_BANDING)
5136 if (!isScrollable())
5137 return false;
5138#endif
5139
5140 if (delegatesScrolling()) {
5141 ScrollPosition oldPosition = scrollPosition();
5142 ScrollPosition newPosition = oldPosition - IntSize(wheelEvent.deltaX(), wheelEvent.deltaY());
5143 if (oldPosition != newPosition) {
5144 ScrollView::scrollTo(newPosition);
5145 scrollPositionChanged(oldPosition, scrollPosition());
5146 didChangeScrollOffset();
5147 }
5148 return true;
5149 }
5150
5151 // We don't allow mouse wheeling to happen in a ScrollView that has had its scrollbars explicitly disabled.
5152 if (!canHaveScrollbars())
5153 return false;
5154
5155 if (platformWidget())
5156 return false;
5157
5158#if ENABLE(ASYNC_SCROLLING)
5159 if (auto scrollingCoordinator = this->scrollingCoordinator()) {
5160 if (scrollingCoordinator->coordinatesScrollingForFrameView(*this))
5161 return scrollingCoordinator->handleWheelEventForScrolling(wheelEvent, scrollingNodeID(), gestureState);
5162 }
5163#endif
5164
5165 return ScrollableArea::handleWheelEventForScrolling(wheelEvent, gestureState);
5166}

5282
5283void FrameView::fireLayoutRelatedMilestonesIfNeeded()
5284{
5285 OptionSet<LayoutMilestone> requestedMilestones;
5286 OptionSet<LayoutMilestone> milestonesAchieved;
5287 Page* page = frame().page();
5288 if (page)
5289 requestedMilestones = page->requestedLayoutMilestones();
5290
5291 if (m_firstLayoutCallbackPending) {
5292 m_firstLayoutCallbackPending = false;
5293 frame().loader().didFirstLayout();
5294 if (requestedMilestones & DidFirstLayout)
5295 milestonesAchieved.add(DidFirstLayout);
5296 if (frame().isMainFrame())
5297 page->startCountingRelevantRepaintedObjects();
5298 }
5299
5300 if (m_firstVisuallyNonEmptyLayoutMilestoneIsPending) {
5301 checkAndDispatchDidReachVisuallyNonEmptyState();
5302 if (m_contentQualifiesAsVisuallyNonEmpty) {
5303 m_firstVisuallyNonEmptyLayoutMilestoneIsPending = false;
5304
5305 addPaintPendingMilestones(DidFirstMeaningfulPaint);
5306 if (requestedMilestones & DidFirstVisuallyNonEmptyLayout)
5307 milestonesAchieved.add(DidFirstVisuallyNonEmptyLayout);
5308 }
5309 }
5310
5311 if (!m_renderedSignificantAmountOfText && qualifiesAsSignificantRenderedText()) {
5312 m_renderedSignificantAmountOfText = true;
5313 if (requestedMilestones & DidRenderSignificantAmountOfText)
5314 milestonesAchieved.add(DidRenderSignificantAmountOfText);
5315 }
5316
5317 if (milestonesAchieved && frame().isMainFrame()) {
5318 if (milestonesAchieved.contains(DidFirstVisuallyNonEmptyLayout))
5319 FRAMEVIEW_RELEASE_LOG(Layout, "fireLayoutRelatedMilestonesIfNeeded: Firing first visually non-empty layout milestone on the main frame");
5320 frame().loader().didReachLayoutMilestone(milestonesAchieved);
5321 }
5322}
5323
5324void FrameView::firePaintRelatedMilestonesIfNeeded()
5325{
5326 Page* page = frame().page();
5327 if (!page)
5328 return;
5329
5330 OptionSet<LayoutMilestone> milestonesAchieved;
5331
5332 // Make sure the pending paint milestones have actually been requested before we send them.
5333 if (m_milestonesPendingPaint & DidFirstFlushForHeaderLayer) {
5334 if (page->requestedLayoutMilestones() & DidFirstFlushForHeaderLayer)
5335 milestonesAchieved.add(DidFirstFlushForHeaderLayer);
5336 }
5337
5338 if (m_milestonesPendingPaint & DidFirstPaintAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering) {
5339 if (page->requestedLayoutMilestones() & DidFirstPaintAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering)
5340 milestonesAchieved.add(DidFirstPaintAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering);
5341 }
5342
5343 if (m_milestonesPendingPaint & DidFirstMeaningfulPaint) {
5344 if (page->requestedLayoutMilestones() & DidFirstMeaningfulPaint)
5345 milestonesAchieved.add(DidFirstMeaningfulPaint);
5346 }
5347
5348 m_milestonesPendingPaint = { };
5349
5350 if (milestonesAchieved)
5351 page->mainFrame().loader().didReachLayoutMilestone(milestonesAchieved);
5352}

5425void FrameView::updateWidgetPositions()
5426{
5427 m_updateWidgetPositionsTimer.stop();
5428 // updateWidgetPosition() can possibly cause layout to be re-entered (via plug-ins running
5429 // scripts in response to NPP_SetWindow, for example), so we need to keep the Widgets
5430 // alive during enumeration.
5431 for (auto& widget : collectAndProtectWidgets(m_widgetsInRenderTree)) {
5432 if (auto* renderer = RenderWidget::find(*widget)) {
5433 auto ignoreWidgetState = renderer->updateWidgetPosition();
5434 UNUSED_PARAM(ignoreWidgetState);
5435 }
5436 }
5437}

5456void FrameView::setViewExposedRect(std::optional<FloatRect> viewExposedRect)
5457{
5458 if (m_viewExposedRect == viewExposedRect)
5459 return;
5460
5461 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Scrolling, stream << "FrameView " << this << " setViewExposedRect " << (viewExposedRect ? viewExposedRect.value() : FloatRect()));
5462
5463 bool hasRectExistenceChanged = !m_viewExposedRect == !viewExposedRect;
5464 m_viewExposedRect = viewExposedRect;
5465
5466 // FIXME: We should support clipping to the exposed rect for subframes as well.
5467 if (!frame().isMainFrame())
5468 return;
5469
5470 if (TiledBacking* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking()) {
5471 if (hasRectExistenceChanged)
5472 updateTiledBackingAdaptiveSizing();
5473 adjustTiledBackingCoverage();
5474 tiledBacking->setTiledScrollingIndicatorPosition(m_viewExposedRect ? m_viewExposedRect.value().location() : FloatPoint());
5475 }
5476
5477 if (auto* page = frame().page()) {
5478 page->scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::LayerFlush);
5479 page->pageOverlayController().didChangeViewExposedRect();
5480 }
5481}

5519IntSize FrameView::viewportSizeForCSSViewportUnits() const
5520{
5521 OverrideViewportSize viewportSize;
5522
5523 if (m_overrideViewportSize) {
5524 viewportSize = *m_overrideViewportSize;
5525 // auto-size overrides the width only, so we can't always bail out early here.
5526 if (viewportSize.width && viewportSize.height)
5527 return { *viewportSize.width, *viewportSize.height };
5528 }
5529
5530 if (useFixedLayout()) {
5531 auto fixedLayoutSize = this->fixedLayoutSize();
5532 viewportSize.width = viewportSize.width.value_or(fixedLayoutSize.width());
5533 viewportSize.height = viewportSize.height.value_or(fixedLayoutSize.height());
5534 return { *viewportSize.width, *viewportSize.height };
5535 }
5536
5537 // FIXME: the value returned should take into account the value of the overflow
5538 // property on the root element.
5539 auto visibleContentSizeIncludingScrollbars = visibleContentRectIncludingScrollbars().size();
5540 viewportSize.width = viewportSize.width.value_or(visibleContentSizeIncludingScrollbars.width());
5541 viewportSize.height = viewportSize.height.value_or(visibleContentSizeIncludingScrollbars.height());
5542 return { *viewportSize.width, *viewportSize.height };
5543}

5571void FrameView::updateScrollbarSteps()
5572{
5573 auto* documentElement = frame().document() ? frame().document()->documentElement() : nullptr;
5574 auto* renderer = documentElement ? documentElement->renderBox() : nullptr;
5575 if (!renderer) {
5576 ScrollView::updateScrollbarSteps();
5577 return;
5578 }
5579
5580 LayoutRect paddedViewRect(LayoutPoint(), visibleSize());
5581 paddedViewRect.contract(renderer->scrollPaddingForViewportRect(paddedViewRect));
5582
5583 if (horizontalScrollbar()) {
5584 int pageStep = Scrollbar::pageStep(paddedViewRect.width());
5585 horizontalScrollbar()->setSteps(Scrollbar::pixelsPerLineStep(), pageStep);
5586
5587 }
5588 if (verticalScrollbar()) {
5589 int pageStep = Scrollbar::pageStep(paddedViewRect.height());
5590 verticalScrollbar()->setSteps(Scrollbar::pixelsPerLineStep(), pageStep);
5591 }
